title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer beans over beef.
Top with tortillas and sprinkle with cheese.
Spread tomatoes over tortillas and pour soup over all.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, garlic and pepper.
Drain well. Mix corn bread, eggs, milk and oil.
Add creamed corn.
Pour half of bread mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add beef mixture, then grated cheese, then the remainder of the bread mix.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large roasting pan or Dutch oven, fry bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Drain fat from pan.
In same pan, cook and stir ground beef, onion and celery until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water and add remaining ingredients into meat mixture.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Crumble bacon over beans before serving.

title: polish bow ties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add flour, enough to form a ball.
Roll out ball.
Cut into 3-inch strips.
Cut strips into 3-inch diamonds.
Cut slit into each diamond.
Curve dough into slit of diamond.
Fry in Crisco oil.
Powder with 4x sugar when cold.

title: cucumber salad(from the four seasons restaurant new york)
directions: Mix all ingredients together ahead and chill. Goes well with cold poached salmon steaks and green sauce.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Combine water, broth and soy sauce in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil. Combine cornstarch and water (2 tablespoons). Stir well. Add to broth mixture. Boil 1 minute over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Combine egg and sherry. Slowly pour egg mixture into boiling soup, stirring constantly (egg forms lacy strands as it cooks). Ladle soup into bowls and sprinkle with green onion. Serve immediately. Yield: 2 2/3 cups.

title: wild rice and ham casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Spread over bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer broccoli over rice.
Sprinkle ham over broccoli, then cover with Cheddar cheese.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and mustard; spread over casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: best ever yellow cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box. Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Remove cake from oven. Punch holes in it. Simmer pineapple and sugar. Pour pineapple mixture over cake. Put in refrigerator to cool. Mix pudding. Add coconut to pudding. Spread coconut/pudding mixture over pineapple. Cover with topping of Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer ingredients in order. Top with Miracle Whip and cheese. Refrigerate overnight.

title: caramel corn
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine butter, syrup and salt.
Heat to boiling and boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Take from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour over popped corn; mix well.
Place in large roasting pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring about every 20 minutes.
"When cool, store in covered container.
Will stay crisp and tender without sticking."

title: orange salad supreme
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add juice from oranges. Add sherbet and blend with mixer to dissolve.
Refrigerate and when partially set, add orange sections.
Put in ring mold if you wish to use it for a salad or into a 9 x 11-inch pan and cut into squares to serve as a dessert with whipped cream.

title: cole slaw for crowd(country:  u. s.)
directions: Spread first 5 ingredients in a large container in order listed.
Pour sugar over top.
(Do not stir.)

title: tomato chili sauce
directions: Wash, peel and quarter the tomatoes.
Put the tomatoes, peppers and onions through a food grinder.
Mix up the remaining ingredients in a large pot and add the vegetables.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 3 hours, stirring frequently.
Makes 15 to 18 pints of chili.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon and reserve some bacon fat (1 to 2 tablespoons). Stir flour into fat.
Add onions and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vinegar and stir.
Add crumbled bacon and sliced potatoes.
Stir several times while heating on low to medium heat until flavors blend (1/2 to 1 hour).
I use electric fry pan.

title: hideaway cupcakes
directions: Prepare filling mix according to package directions for pie using 1/2 the liquid; cool.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper cupcake wrappers.
Sift flour with sugar and baking powder into bowl.
Add butter and milk; blend well at low speed for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add egg and vanilla and beat another 1 1/2 minutes at low.
Fill baking cups half full.
Top with teaspoon of filling (reserve remaining filling for topping).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until cake springs back when touched lightly in center. Cool and spread with remaining filling.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion and cook for a minute longer.
Mix in corn, mushroom soup, sour cream, salt, pepper, garlic powder, sliced mushrooms and cooked noodles.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Over low heat, melt butter and marshmallows.
Stir until completely mixed.
Add Jell-O.
Stir popcorn in gently.
Form into popcorn balls.
Wrap separately.
Use colored Jell-O for holiday treats (orange for Halloween, red and green for Christmas, etc.).

title: kraut chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water to egg mixture.
Stir in kraut.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 8-inch square or round pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cover with your favorite icing.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat
oven
In large bowl, combine filling ingredients.
Mix
well and turn into shell.
Bake 15 minutes, then
reduce
oven temperature to 350°.
Continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean. Cool
before
cutting.
Garnish with whipped cream and nuts. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: special occasion punch
directions: Pour half of the apricot nectar and pineapple juice into punch bowl. Break up pieces of orange sherbet and add to juice (about 1/2 container).
Pour soda over sherbet and juices just before serving.
You can add remaining juices and sherbet as needed.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups water.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook for 10 to 15 minutes in a saucepan.
Add to cooked rice. Pour into a greased casserole dish; cover with foil and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk and water.
Beat.
Add eggs and cook at medium heat, stirring with wooden spoon until thick. Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.
Leave out cocoa for other cream pies.

title: cheesy artichoke heart appetizers
directions: Unroll dough and press into bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread over crust. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Yields 3 dozen.

title: golden gate carrot cake
directions: Sift first four ingredients together.
Beat eggs; add oil, buttermilk, sugar and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in pineapple, carrots, nuts, coconut and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Slowly pour glaze over hot cake until it is absorbed.

title: new new potatoes
directions: Saute potatoes until golden; add mushrooms; continue to saute until mushrooms begin to brown.
Mix 2 tablespoons white wine with enough water to make 1/2 cup; pour over potatoes and other ingredients.
Cover and let simmer until tender (stir occasionally).
Cooking time approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Glaze while still warm.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen, depending on size of cutter.

title: flaming plum pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine suet, fruits, bread crumbs, spices, salt, sugar and raspberries and mix well.
Beat eggs until foamy; stir in milk, cognac and white wine.
With rubber scraper, fold egg mixture into fruit mixture until well blended.
Turn batter into well-greased 2-quart pudding mold with tight fitting cover. Place mold on a trivet in a large kettle.
Pour in enough boiling water to come halfway up side of mold.
Cover pot.
Steam pudding 4 hours.
Water in kettle should boil gently.
Add more water as needed.
Remove pudding to wire rack; let cool about 5 minutes. Invert on serving plate.
Lift off mold.
Flame serve with hard sauce.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Place tomatoes and tomato sauce or paste into 4-quart saucepan. Cook until well done, about 30 minutes. Next, add chopped peppers, onions, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce to taste. Simmer until peppers and onions are tender. Place in sterilized jars and seal.

title: red cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs. Make paste of coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture. Add salt, buttermilk, flour and vanilla. Beat. Remove from mixer. Add vinegar and soda. Mix, but don't beat. Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red cabbage slaw
directions: In a large bowl, toss together all ingredients.
Makes 4 cups.

title: hawaiian rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Then fold in whipped cream and chill.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Very moist and very good.

title: chocolate browney pie
directions: Pat sumpin in a bowl.
Put egg in it and you crack.
Put some water in it and you do this (stir), then it will look like rocks; you put it in a pan that's round and cook it a long time, maybe 5 minutes.
You take it out and put holes in it to see if it's done. You take it outside so it will cool.
When it's not hot, you put frosting on.

title: baked ribs and dressing
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except spareribs. Add more water if a moist stuffing is desired.
Place dressing in the bottom of a greased baking dish.
Place ribs on top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: garden of eden syrup for waffles, etc.
directions: In small saucepan, combine the juice concentrate and figs or dates.
Heat over low heat 5 minutes to soften fruit, then pour into blender.
Mix on high 1 minute, until fruit is pureed. Return to saucepan.
Add cornstarch and vanilla and heat over low heat until thickened.
Serve warm.
An alternative of maple syrup most kids like.

title: swedish cabbage rolls
directions: Pour over cabbage rolls.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham and cheese fondue casserole(serves 6)
directions: Make a layer of 1/3 of the bread, ham and cheese cubes in a buttered, straight side 8-cup baking dish.
Mix flour and mustard in a cup; sprinkle about 1 tablespoonful over layer; drizzle 1 tablespoonful of melted butter or margarine over.
Repeat with remaining bread, ham, cheese, flour mixture and butter mixture to make 2 more layers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut up the biscuits into 1/4 sections.
Roll them in 1/2 cup sugar and the cinnamon.
Put into greased Bundt pan; put aside. Over medium heat, cook 3/4 cup sugar, the butter and vanilla. Stir until boiling.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool 10 minutes, then invert onto serving plate.

title: minnesota casserole
directions: Brown together hamburger, onion and celery.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour or more until rice is done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake in casserole dish until it bubbles up all over.
Then remove from oven and sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Pour 1/2 stick melted margarine over top.
Let brown slightly.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together with mixer until fluffy.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice together three times. By hand, add flour to the creamed mixture alternately with milk. Add cream.
In a separate bowl, pour bourbon on nuts and allow to soak.
Next, add vanilla, egg yellows and preserves.
Beat the egg whites with electric mixer.
Add the nuts and bourbon to the batter.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into three greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean and thinly slice the fresh mushrooms.
Place all other ingredients into a jar and shake well.
Pour over the mushrooms and marinate overnight.
Spoon over lettuce wedges or mixed greens as a salad dressing.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix sausage, grated cheese, cayenne pepper and Bisquick until well blended.
Make into marble size balls.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Saute sauce and beef; drain grease.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Combine tomatoes, meat mixture, onion and green pepper. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer, the longer the better.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Add to the egg yolks, a little at a time, mixing well, then add cocoa and water, then butter and vanilla.
Bake at 375° in preheated oven.

title: fruity floats
directions: Dilute punch concentrate, using package directions.
Chill well.
Place small scoop of ice cream in a chilled tall glass. Add 1/2 to 3/4 cup chilled punch; stir slightly.
Top with additional ice cream.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: irish brown soda bread
directions: Sift flours, salt and baking soda together.
Stir in oats. Make a well and pour in buttermilk.
Stir with wooden spoon until soft, moist dough forms.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface. Form it into an 8-inch rounded disk.
With sharp knife, cut a deep cross through dough, cutting it almost into quarters.
Bake on buttered sheet at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer or until bread is crusty.
Cool on rack.

title: graham cracker cherry dessert(for diabetics)
directions: Crush graham crackers in fine crumbs.
Line bottom of an 8-inch square baking pan with half of the crumbs.
Refrigerate. In saucepan, combine crushed pineapple in its own juice and the cornstarch.
Stir to blend.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Cool completely.
Fold in walnuts.
Now spread mixture over the top of the crumbs in the pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Lightly pat down the surface.
Refrigerate.
Make gelatin as directed on package.
Allow gelatin to set to the consistency of egg whites.
Pour over the top layer of crumbs.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 8 people.
Calories:
1 serving = 105 calories.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion for 10 minutes.
In a bowl, mix soup, sour cream, carrots, squash and onions.
Melt butter and pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add 1/2 the stuffing mix.
Pour squash mixture over the top.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creamy jello salad
directions: Add Jell-O to Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Use mixer to blend.
Drain can of pineapple tidbits, then stir pineapple into mixture.
Put in bowl and chill for several hours.
May use light Cool Whip and fat-free cottage cheese for "light" treat.

title: brandied goose
directions: Marinate goose overnight in brandy to tenderize and eliminate gamey flavor.
Save the brandy.
Roll pieces of goose in flour and brown in oil and butter in a Dutch oven.
Brown a few pieces at a time.
Add bouillon, steak sauce, sherry, marjoram, salt, pepper and bay leaves to the pan.
Heat.
Return the goose to pan.
Cover and place in a 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove goose from pan.
Mix cornstarch with cherries and add to pan juices with brandy.
Stir and heat over low flame until sauce is slightly thickened.
Return meat and baste with sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes, basting several times.
Place goose on a heated platter and spoon a little sauce over each piece.
Serve rest of sauce in a gravy boat to be ladled over hot goose.

title: tamale chili
directions: Cut up beef tamales after removing paper from each one.
Add other ingredients.
Place in slow cooker for several hours until good and done.

title: super biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make biscuits; place on greased pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: saffron rice with almonds
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter in a medium size skillet on medium heat.
When hot, saut celery and onions until lightly coated with the butter (4 to 5 minutes).
Add the rice and cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute more.
Add the chicken stock, salt, pepper and saffron.
Stir in the raisins and almonds.
Place in buttered casserole; cover and bake at 350° until all liquid is absorbent, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(This dish can be prepared and held, covered in a 250° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.)

title: baked zucchini
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: spicy nuts
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg white and cream of tartar until it forms stiff peaks.
Beat in 1 tablespoon water and 1/2 cup sugar. Then add in cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, ground cloves, mace, salt and pepper.
Mix it all up, folding in the walnuts.
Spread out on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes, tossing every 10 minutes.
Cool and store in a tin.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Mix together zucchini, egg, cheese, onion and garlic. Place zucchini mix over 1 cup of cracker crumbs in an 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crackers.
Spray Pam lightly to avoid sticking.
Bake 1 hour.

title: baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken in cold water.
Place in a glass baking dish. Drizzle margarine over chicken.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Cover and bake 50 to 60 minutes until wings move easily to touch.

title: french fries
directions: Fry potatoes, onions and wieners together.

title: catsup
directions: Boil until soft and strain; add spices.
Boil 3 hours.
If not thick, use a little cornstarch.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine pineapple and eggs; mix together sugar, flour and salt and add to pineapple.
Pour into buttered casserole dish; toss bread cubes into melted margarine and place on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pierogi dough
directions: Mix eggs, sour cream and salt.
Add flour and warm water; mix until dough feels like velvet.
Roll out thin sheets.
Cut circles; put filling on 1/2 of circle.
Fold over and crimp edges with fork.
Cook in boiling water until they rise to top.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: cheryl's infamous cheese cake
directions: Mix all together in a bowl and blend at high speed with an electric mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: double duty dish salad
directions: Pour dry jello over cottage cheese.
Pour directly from package.
Drain pineapple and oranges, then mix in the Cool Whip.

title: granola bars
directions: Mix peanut butter, honey, margarine and vanilla, then add all other ingredients and mix well.
Press hard in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Press ingredients down again.
Cut when cool.
Put pan in fridge.
Eat when cold.
Keep uneaten bars in fridge until all eaten.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Gradually add scalded milk, stirring constantly.
Pour into pastry shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is set.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onions.
Place in a saucepan.
Add 2 cups of water and bring to a boil.
Add salt and cover.
Cook until tender and drain.
Place potatoes in a baking dish.
Melt margarine in a saucepan and blend in flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Fold in cheese and stir until melted.
Pour the cheese sauce over the potatoes and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° until bubbly and brown.

title: frozen strawberry meringue
directions: Crushed strawberries:
Wash berries under cold, running water. Remove hulls; drain.
Put berries into a small bowl.
Mash with a potato masher or the rim of a glass.
Set aside 1 cup to beat into the meringue.
Sweeten remaining crushed berries to taste with powdered sugar or honey.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: baked rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Add rice.
Stir over moderate heat until rice is golden.
Add salt.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; add to rice.

title: double chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, milk, chocolate chips and butter in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into shell and chill 3 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter and powdered sugar together.
Spread half the mixture on the bottom of the pie shell.
Spread pudding in pie shell with Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle rest of peanut butter mixture on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix cake.
Pour into 9 x 13 in glass dish sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350 until done.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Wash chicken and place in a shallow dish.
Pour buttermilk over chicken; cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, pour off buttermilk and pat chicken dry with paper towels. Melt butter with tarragon.
Add lemon juice.
Add parsley and sesame seed and seasoned salt to bread crumbs and mix well.
Dip chicken in butter; then coat with bread crumbs.
Arrange in a baking dish.
Spoon remaining butter over chicken.
Cover tightly and refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake at 350° without turning about 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally with drippings.

title: franke's egg custard pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat 2 eggs 2 minutes then add 2 more eggs and beat 2 more minutes.
Add milk, vanilla, salt and nutmeg.
Pour mixture into unbaked shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Turn down to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese dip
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add cheese, mushrooms and soup. Cook over low heat until thick.
(Can be done in microwave.) Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Makes a large crock-pot full.

title: fluffy salmon cakes
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Mix with potatoes.
Beat in eggs, seasonings and butter.
Shape into cakes or rolls and fry in deep, hot fat.
Serve hot.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Make tiny meatballs (with garlic salt).
Melt ketchup, jelly and lemon juice.
Add meatballs and simmer for 1 hour.

title: snickerdoodles light lowered-fat cookies
directions: Beat margarine and 1 1/2 cups sugar until fluffy.
Add milk and egg whites.
Beat again.
Add flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Beat until well mixed.
In a shallow dish, combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.

title: nutty apple dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Serve with sliced apples for dipping.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Remove from heat. Add salt, pepper and oleo; mix.
Add cracker crumbs, milk, egg and 1/2 the cheese.
Mix.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Partially cook sausage; grate cheese.
Mix and work all ingredients together.
Form into balls and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Over low heat, stirring constantly, bring first 3 ingredients to a boil. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add
sugar and vanilla.

title: midwest vegetable crunch salad
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients. Pour dressing over.
Marinate in the dressing for four hours or overnight in the refrigerator. When ready to serve, add Bac*Os mix and eat.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Shell the shrimp and cut them crosswise into 1/2 inch pieces. Mix shrimp with cornstarch and salt in bowl.
Heat wok on high. Add oil.
Cook shrimp 10 seconds.
Turn heat to medium and stir briskly.
Pour in dish.
Clean pan.
Add oil.
Pour in eggs.
When fluffy, scoop in dish.
Clean pan.
Set pan on medium.
Add cooked rice; toss 1 minute.
Sprinkle salt and add scallions, eggs and shrimp last.
Pour in hot serving dish.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In a saucepan, cover carrots with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until barely tender; drain.
Melt butter with marmalade and jelly, stirring until all are blended.
Add carrots; cook together for a few minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hawaiian flank steak
directions: Combine all ingredients, except steak, in a small saucepan; cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Score steak in a diamond pattern, 1/8-inch deep.
Place steak and marinade in plastic bag, turning to coat.
Tie bag tightly, forcing air out; place in dish. Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight, turning at least once.

title: buffet bread
directions: Cut bread lengthwise, but not all the way through.
Soften butter and mix in parsley and green onion.
Spread mixture in center of bread.
Close bread and wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes or until butter melts.
Slice and serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: butter cream frosting
directions: Place 3 cups sugar, butter, shortening, 4 tablespoons milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining 3 cups sugar; beat at medium speed until light and fluffy; add more milk 1 tablespoon at a time as needed for good spreading consistency.
Makes about 3-1/2 cups.

title: melba cheesecake pie
directions: Microwave margarine in pie plate 1/2 to 1 minute or until melted. Mix in crumbs and 2 tablespoons sugar; press onto bottom and sides of pie plate. Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Arrange peaches on crust.

title: easy potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes
and cut into wedges. Place on a cookie sheet and spray each wedge with Pam. Sprinkle each wedge with garlic and Lawry's. Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: dena's delirious bean dip
directions: Place beans in a 9-inch glass casserole.
Layer with sour cream and guacamole.
Add grated cheese followed by tomatoes and black olives.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill for one hour. Serve dip with the tortilla chips and enjoy!

title: chicken supreme
directions: Tear chipped beef into small bits and place in bottom of flat 2 qt. baking pan.
Wrap bacon around each chicken breast.
Place on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and cover the chicken completely.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 3 hours.
Glass pan will bake casserole in less time.

title: pot roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with a tenderizer.
Let stand 2 hours.
Brown roast on both sides in part of margarine.
Bury garlic buttons in folds of meat.
Saturate meat with 1 stick of melted margarine and Worcestershire sauce.
Wrap tightly in foil and cook at 325° until done.
This depends on size of roast.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly. Spoon off excess fat. Add next 5 ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles as directed. Drain and rinse. Combine remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese. Place 1/2 noodles in 9 x 13. Spread 1/2 cottage cheese filling. Add 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat sauce. Repeat layers. Bake at 375° about 30 minutes. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and let get soft.
Mix with sausage and Bisquick. Make into balls and bake at 350° until done.

title: faultless fudge (microwave)
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add milk and butter.
Cook on High 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave, add vanilla and nuts.
Stir ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into a greased dish and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: wednesday's chili
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add onion.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: twice baked potato
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Place the potatoes on a cutting board. With the tip of small, sharp knife, score a lid shape on the top of each potato about 1/3 of the way down, cutting in about 1/8-inch all the way around.

title: sweet 'n sour potato medley
directions: Cook bacon in 10-inch skillet until crisp. Drain and crumble. Stir soup, water, sugar, vinegar, garlic and pepper sauce into skillet.
Stir in potato slices and sauce mix from au gratin potato package and carrots.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender, about 25 minutes.
Stir in peas.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Stir in tomatoes.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add remainder of ingredients in order given.
Beat well.
Place in well-greased and floured pan.
Bake in cold oven at 325° for 90 minutes.
Take out of pan while hot.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: On top of a double broiler over simmering water, beat the egg yolks and salt. Add the sugar, milk, and butter. As soon as the bottom pot boils, mix the cornstarch with a small amount of water. Add it to the egg yolk mixture a little at a time. Cook until thick, stirring constantly with a wire whisk.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed using 2 pans.
When completely cool, split each layer in half.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut. Chill.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Store in airtight cake container for 3 days before serving.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Place alternating layers of shrimp, onion, and capers in a bowl.
Combine oil, vinegar, celery seed, salt and Tabasco.
Pour over shrimp mixture, cover, and chill at least 8 hours.
Drain shrimp before serving.
Serve in a bowl set in another bowl containing ice chips.

title: crab meat mousse
directions: Add gelatine to cold water.
Heat soup; stir in gelatine.
Stir until you are sure gelatine is dissolved.
Add cream cheese and mayonnaise and beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill.
Serve with Club crackers.

title: quick butterscotch brownies(these brownies have a unique taste.)
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan, then remove from heat and blend in sugar.
Cool slightly.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well mixed. Pour into a well-greased and lightly floured pan (9 x 13-inch) and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle some crushed chips on top of casserole.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Roll crackers to fine crumbs; add sugar.
Mix; melt margarine and add to crumbs.
Mix.
Grease pan; press crumb mix into pan, saving a little for the top.
Freeze at least 30 minutes.
Pour pudding mix into pan and top with crumbs.
Chill.

title: strawberry pie glaze
directions: Mash 1/2 of strawberries in pan on low heat.
Combine cornstarch with sugar and add to mashed strawberries.
Add lemon juice.
Stir until thick and it comes to a boil.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mud flat pie
directions: Mix flour, pecans, sugar and butter together and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan for the crust.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° and cool.
Mix confectioners sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese and spread over crust.
Mix chocolate pudding and cold milk and spread over filling.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Core and peel apples. Cut into chunks about 1 inch. Mix sugar and cinnamon and then with apples. Set aside.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 12 inch metal or glass dish.
Remove pan from oven and add peaches.
In a separate container, mix milk, sugar, vanilla and flour.
Pour this mixture over peaches and butter.
Do not stir.
Bake 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until crust forms and slightly browns.

title: zippy carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix mayonnaise, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper together.
Add to carrots.
Stir.

title: fruit bars
directions: Bake the cookie dough as directed. Cool first. Then mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and Cool Whip. Spread over cookie dough. Top with fruit.

title: apple dapple
directions: Cream 2 sticks of butter or oleo and sugar; mix in eggs.
Add and beat well, flour, cinnamon, baking soda and vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
While cake is baking, boil 1 1/2 minutes, brown sugar, 1 stick butter and milk.
When cake is done, prick top with fork and then pour mix over top.

title: monkey bread
directions: Make mixture of the 3 tablespoons of cinnamon and 4 tablespoons of sugar.
Next, cut each biscuit into quarters and drop into sugar mixture.
Only coat 6 to 8 pieces at a time.
Drop into layers in an ungreased Bundt pan.

title: rice krispies pudding cups
directions: Melt margarine in a large pan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal. Stir until coated.
Press mixture into 16 muffin-pan cups coated with cooking spray.
Cool in refrigerator about 15 minutes. Prepare pudding according to package directions, using skim milk. Divide evenly into 16 cereal cups.
Serve immediately.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well with mixer and pour into floured pan to bake until done (until springy) at 325°.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add onion, carrots and celery.
Simmer several minutes.
Blend in flour quickly.
Add salt, paprika and Old Bay.
Gradually add broth and milk while stirring.
Add seafood and simmer 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let stand until room temperature.
Mix together and roll in nuts.

title: lazy man pie
directions: Pour fruit with juice in bottom of casserole dish.
Then, in mixing bowl, fold butter, sugar and flour until smooth.
Pour mixture over fruit.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: carrot custard pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add eggs, milk carrots, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well; pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until custard is set. Serve warm or cold.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, 1/2 can of fried onion rings and soup in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fork cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pinch off small balls. Using a fork dipped in water, press tops after placed on cookie sheet.
Bake until brown.
Oven heat:
Approximately 325°.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread.
Combine with other ingredients. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and pour over meat during the last 30 minutes of roasting.
Also good on chicken (fried) 15 minutes before serving.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Layer chicken in baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter and add crackers and poppy seed.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice/noodles.

title: fresh blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend in 1/2 cup sugar and the cornstarch in a medium saucepan.
Stir in blueberries and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole; place in oven while preparing biscuit topping.

title: sauerbraten(german recipe)
directions: In a frying pan saute onions, carrots, garlic, celery and pepper in 2 tablespoons of oil until soft.
Add wine vinegar, wine, brown sugar, salt, bay leaf, and pickling spice; allow to cool in a glass or ceramic bowl.
When mixture is cool, submerge roast and marinate for 2 days, covered, in the refrigerator; turn frequently.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add creamed mixture and dry ingredients alternately to canned pumpkin.
Add chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cream of vegetable chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken in 5 cups boiling water 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove meat from bones when cool.
Take fat from top of cool broth. Heat broth and add bouillon cubes, Mrs. Dash, vegetables, onion, celery and potato.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Add soup, water and chicken pieces that have been cut into small pieces.
Heat well.

title: eclair pie
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put a layer of graham crackers, whole. Mix pudding with milk at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 over graham crackers.
Put a second layer of crackers and pour remaining pudding over the crackers.
Cover with a third layer of crackers.	Refrigerate 2 hours and frost with chocolate canned frosting.

title: fudgy cheesecake swirl brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In medium size heavy saucepan over low heat, combine butter and chocolate baking bars.
Heat for 3 minutes, or until melted, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat; cool 10 minutes.
Stir in 1 3/4 cups sugar.
Beat in 3 eggs.
Stir in flour until blended.
Spread batter into prepared baking pan.

title: quick cream cheese braid
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Unroll 1 can of crescent rolls. Press and cover bottom of baking pan.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add milk alternately with flour which has been sifted with baking powder.
Use 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baby food pound cake
directions: Mix well together.
Grease and flour Bundt or cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry cobbler bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/4 cup butter and eggs, mixing well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan that is greased on the bottom.
Pour pie filling over, smoothing well.
Combine frosting mix and remaining butter.
Sprinkle over cherries.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown hamburger meat (can substitute ground turkey or sliced chicken).
Add the can of enchilada sauce, 2 cans of mushroom soup, the water and the Velveeta cheese.
Continue heating and stir until the cheese is melted and mixed well.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: In small bowl, pour boiling water over chocolate; let stand 20 minutes to cool.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 325°.
Grease well and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
In large bowl, at high speed, beat softened butter, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture alternately with sour cream (begin and end with flour). Beat in cooled chocolate mixture until combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes, until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Transfer to rack.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes one loaf.

title: cheese breadsticks
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients except egg and water; stir until mixture doesn't stick to the bowl.
Knead dough for about 1 minute very lightly.
Divide into 24 equal pieces. Roll into 6-inch ropes and twist 2 ropes together.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Make an egg wash with the egg and water; brush on breadsticks.
Bake for 12 to 17 minutes.
Remove as soon as sticks become a light golden brown color.

title: fresh fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add fruit and juice.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like "meal".
Stir in milk.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot fruit.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: gracie's peanut butter fudge
directions: Put first three ingredients in pan.
Place on low heat; stir to dissolve sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 8 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until creamy.
Pour into greased pan.
Cut when cool.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook green pepper, celery and onions in butter for 10 minutes. Add soup and milk.
Blend and heat through.
Add cheese; heat until cheese melts.
Cook and drain noodles.
Combine noodles and 1/3 of soup mixture.
Turn noodles into baking pan.

title: sour cream-blueberry coffee cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer 2 minutes or until creamy. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating 2 to 3 minutes. Add eggs and next 3 ingredients, beating until smooth. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture, beating until blended. Pour batter into a lightly greased 9-inch spring-form pan. Combine blueberries and next 3 ingredients. Sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool on wire rack 10 minutes. Whisk together powdered sugar and milk until smooth. Drizzle over cake. Yield: 1 (9-inch) cake.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add lemon juice to apples.
Add sugar and spice mixture to apples.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell; dot top of apples with butter.
Add top pastry to pie.
Sprinkle sugar on top of pastry.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Add rice and stir to coat. Stir remaining ingredients into dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Add small amount of water as necessary during baking time. Serves 8.

title: farmer's omelet
directions: In 12-inch skillet (double wrap handle with aluminum foil) on medium heat, add oil.
Add potatoes and cook 8 minutes, until tender and golden brown.
Meanwhile, with wire whisk, beat eggs, milk, basil and pepper until well blended; set aside.
Heat broiler.
When potatoes are tender, add tomatoes, bacon and peas to skillet and pour egg mixture over it.
Reduce heat to medium and cook approximately 12 minutes until eggs are almost set.
Place skillet under broiler 5 to 6 inches from heat source.
Broil until top is set and golden and knife inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from broiler and sprinkle with cheese.
Serve hot.

title: cheddar dill bread
directions: In large bowl, combine the flours, baking powder, salt, dill, celery seed, pepper, cheese and onions.
Mix the egg and milk together in another bowl and add the liquid to the dry ingredients.
Mix just enough to combine completely.
Spoon the batter into greased pans.
Bake in 375° oven until a tester comes out clean.
Cool in the pans for 10 minutes.
Remove to a rack to cool completely.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water. Add the ice cubes and mix well. Add the pineapple, pecans, cherries and Coke. Stir and mix well. Congeal in icebox.

title: double decker fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil.
Place 1 cup peanut butter chips in medium bowl; set aside.
In second medium bowl, blend melted butter, cocoa and vanilla until smooth.
Add 1 cup peanut butter chips.

title: southern nut dessert
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until light.
Slowly beat in sugar and baking powder.
Continue beating for 5 minutes, until light and lemon colored.
Mix in nuts.
Generously butter 8-inch square pan.
Pour in mixture.
Smooth top evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until top feels dry.
Cool.
Press dry "shell" on top down.
Cut into squares.
Top with fruit and whipped cream.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with 1 1/2 cups crushed potato chips, 4 ounces grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: raspberry swirls
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together, work in the flour. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Mix ingredients for filling & set aside. Roll out the dough (1/2 at a time) as for jelly roll.
Spread 1/2 the filling on and roll up.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice 1/2 inch thick and bake on greased sheet at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar with beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add together and add apples.
Mix well. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in an airtight container. Use 1/3 cup of mix per cup of boiling water.

title: stir-fry style chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Cut pepper into strips.
Divide onion into rings.
On a sheet of heavy-duty foil, place chicken breast with soy sauce and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Top with vegetables and water.
Sprinkle with parsley and salt and add garlic powder to taste.
Wrap in foil, using 1 layer of wet paper and foil.
Place on coals for 1/2 hour, turning in 15 minutes. Makes one serving.

title: special cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: aunt juanita's 5 cup salad
directions: Mix; chill and serve.

title: perfectly easy pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw bread dough until soft.
Beat egg with fork.
Add cheese, parsley and pepperoni.
Mix well.
Roll out bread dough to about 7 x 12 inches.
Spread pepperoni mixture evenly over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll, starting at 12-inch end.
Place on greased cookie sheet or 13-inch pan, seam side down.
Tuck ends in.
Let raise 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
If soft crust is desired, brush with soft butter while still warm, then cover with dish towel.

title: mary kay potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: baked chicken breast fillet
directions: Wash and pat chicken dry.
Dip in melted butter; coat with cracker crumbs.
Place on baking dish or pan.
Pour any extra butter or crumbs over top.
Cover lightly with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: slush punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Combine sugar mixture, pineapple juice and next 2 ingredients in a large container; freeze.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.
Place in a punch bowl and break into chunks; add ginger ale.
Stir until slushy.
Yields 5 1/2 quarts.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix first six ingredients together and shape into small meatballs.
Heat tomato sauce, water, cranberry sauce and mushrooms, plus juice together.
Heat well until cranberry sauce melts.
Add meatballs, cover and cook one hour.
Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: block party beans
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown beef.
Drain fat.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and ketchup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Put in large roaster.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 25 servings.

title: tuna noodle pie
directions: Combine noodles, Parmesan cheese, eggs and seasonings; mix well.
In greased 9-inch pie plate, layer half of noodle mixture and Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add vegetables, tuna and Parmesan cheese.
Stir over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Cut pie in wedges and serve with sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
In another bowl, beat eggs, then stir in whipping cream.
Add melted butter and stir; gradually add sugar mixture, stirring until smooth.
Stir in corn. Pour into lightly greased casserole (13 x 9).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until top is deep golden brown and set.

title: jack's favorite smothered quail or dove
directions: Wash quail or dove in cold water and pat dry with paper towel. Salt, pepper and dust with flour.
Brown in mixture of half butter and half Crisco.
Place birds in roaster and cover with water to which a tablespoon of Worcestershire and 2 tablespoons of lemon juice have been added.
Cover roaster and cook in 250° oven until tender, but not falling apart, approximately 2 1/2 hours. If thicker gravy is desired, remove birds when done and add additional flour and cook slowly.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix and beat well.
Pour in 3 greased round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: gloria brown chicken recipe
directions: Dip chicken pieces in melted butter and place in crock-pot. Sprinkle dry Italian dressing on chicken in crock-pot.
Cook on low 5 to 6 hours.
Half an hour before serving, melt cream cheese in mushroom soup in a saucepan and add onion.
When blended well, pour over chicken in crock-pot and cook for remaining 30 minutes. Put cooked rice or noodles in a rectangular casserole and pour chicken and gravy over.

title: bisquick ready mix
directions: Add 2/3 cup milk to 2 cups flour mixture to complete Ready Mix. Dry ingredients will store well in covered container.

title: apple butter
directions: Core, peel and slice apples.
Add only enough water to cook apples until soft.
Press through a sieve, then processor until smooth.
Measure pulp.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook for about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir frequently to prevent burning.
Put into sterilized jars with 1/2 inch left at top.
Put on cap: screw band tight.
Process for 10 minutes in hot water bath.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Pour oil in 9 x 13-inch pan and spread out evenly over bottom. Stir in rest of ingredients with fork or spoon until blended. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar. Beat in egg. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Form dough into small balls. Dip in granulated sugar.
Flatten slightly and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Butter sides of a heavy saucepan.
In it, combine sugars, corn syrup and milk.
Heat and stir over medium heat until sugars dissolve and mixture comes to a boil. Cook to soft ball (234°) stage, stirring occasionally.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat by hand 2 minutes. Add pecans and beat until mixture loses its gloss. Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
If candy becomes too stiff, add a teaspoon or so of hot water.

title: steak alamode
directions: Cut steak into bite-size pieces.
Put flour, salt and pepper on steak; brown in oil.
Add water and simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
Add more water if needed.
Add soups and cook until thick.
Serve on toast or favorite bread.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well and store in dry containers. This is a great holiday gift idea.
Pack in small fancy jars with ribbons or can be given as friendship or love gifts.

title: green bean surprise
directions: Boil green beans 15 minutes.
Add carrots and boil for 10 more minutes.
Drain beans and carrots.
In skillet add diced onions and mushrooms to beans and carrots.
Stir-fry in butter, oil and soy sauce.
Add Swanson chicken and Season-All to taste.
Cook 20 minutes, covered.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Place all ingredients except cheese and meat in blender.
Mix for a few seconds.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and meat and push gently below the surface with back of a spoon.
Pie pan will be full to the rim.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Allow to set for 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: martha washington bonbons
directions: Mix melted margarine with milk and vanilla.
Add 1 box powdered sugar.

Add coconut and nuts. Gradually add other sugar. Chill in refrigerator for about 1 to 2 hours, then form small balls about 1/2 to 1-inch and place onto buttered cookie sheet. Chill for 1 to 2 hours and place toothpick into center of each and chill again.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips. Dip coconut balls into melted chocolate mixture.
Place onto cookie sheet.
After short time (1 to 2 minutes), you may remove toothpicks and enjoy!

title: hamburger-rice casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, bell pepper and rice.
Add salt and chili powder.
Add tomatoes.
Place in a 2-quart greased dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: bacon and cheese appetizers
directions: Grind or use food processor on bacon, onion and cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce and mix. Spread crackers on baking sheet and broil at 500° until brown and bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (save broth).
Pull chicken off bones.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Spread sour cream over chicken and put aside.
Mix onion, celery and butter with chicken broth and boil until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add stuffing mix and mix well together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil, then cover and simmer 1 hour.
Brown 3 cups
onions
in
Crisco.
Add 1 clove garlic and 1 small can mushroom	pieces	and
stems.
Pour into sauce and cook 2 hours longer.
A little water may be added if sauce gets too thick.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and salt.
Add lemon juice and extract.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: quick cook cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put Crisco or Wesson oil in iron skillet and heat in hot oven or use 13 x 9-inch aluminum pan.
Beat eggs in small bowl, adding sugar.
Put cornmeal, flour and buttermilk in mixing bowl.
Stir, mixing thoroughly.
Add hot oil and stir in well.
Add boiling water.
Mix well (batter will be thin).

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch round layer pans.
Sift dry ingredients together into large bowl.
Add shortening and 1/2 can of soup.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add remaining soup and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes more, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Frost with your favorite white frosting.

title: brownies
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: soy ginger glazed chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and remove skin.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, bring 3/4 cup water to a boil and add remaining ingredients.
Add chicken and reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Remove cover and cook over high heat, turning frequently, until liquid turns thick and syrupy and chicken is coated with brown glaze.
Continue to cook until chicken is done. Serves 5 to 7.
Easy; can be prepared ahead.

title: a feed the crowd casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and
cook
until tender, but not brown. Add corn, soups, sour cream, pimientos and seasonings. Mix well. Stir
in cooked noodles.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole. Sprinkle crumbs
over
top.
Bake
minutes
or until hot in 350° oven.	Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix together and pour in an unbaked pie crust.
Cook until done.
Makes its own top.

title: impossible brunch pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Spread vegetable in plate.
Beat sour cream, cottage cheese, Bisquick, butter and eggs until smooth.
Pour over vegetable.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Take the biscuits out of the containers and cut into quarters. Mix an equal amount of sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag. Place some of the biscuit quarters into the cinnamon/sugar mixture and shake.
Continue until all biscuit quarters are covered with cinnamon and sugar.
Place into a Bundt cake pan or baking dish. Melt brown sugar in margarine and pour over the top of the cinnamon biscuits.
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: beets in honey sauce
directions: Put beets in a bowl; set aside.
Combine cornstarch with salt in small saucepan; stir in beet juice.
Add vinegar, honey and oil.
Cook slowly over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add sauce to beets; let stand 10 minutes, then reheat. Serves 8.

title: swiss cheese bake
directions: Slice French bread in 3/4-inch slices and spread with mixture of butter, minced onion, mustard, poppy seed and lemon juice. Insert cheese and corned beef or ham slices in cuts.
Press back into loaf shape and place on greased foil.
Arrange bacon on top. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven; add water and 2 teaspoons salt. Cook until chicken is very tender.
Remove chicken from broth and cool.
Bone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Set aside.

title: double-good fruit shake
directions: In blender container or food processor bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and process on high speed until thick and blended, about 30 seconds.
To carry, pour into chilled thermos containers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise, onion and cheese.
Mix well.
Add broccoli. Pour into buttered casserole and bake in oven at 350° until set. Remove from oven.
Cover with chips or crackers and bake until light brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: 24 hour crisp cole slaw
directions: Put cabbage, pepper and onion in large bowl.
Sprinkle salt and sugar over mixture; let stand 30 minutes.
Heat remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture. Cool; seal tightly and refrigerate.
Best when served after 24 hours in refrigerator.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook meat, onions and green pepper in a skillet until meat is slightly browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese and simmer 30 minutes.
Add cheese. Stir until melted.
Pour into a large greased baking dish.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs; stir in milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat in oil and add corn. Fry in hot oil in frying pan. Delicious served with butter and warm maple syrup.

title: "hot" german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon, then remove from pan when done.
Saute onions and celery in bacon drippings until limp.
Add salt, sugar, pepper, dry mustard, water and vinegar.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Crumble bacon, then add bacon, potatoes and mayonnaise to seasoned sauce. Heat slowly on top of stove (or heat in a 300° oven for 20 minutes).
Top with sausage and serve.

title: sausage balls with cheese i
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix cheese, sausage, water and Bisquick together.
Roll into medium balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 50 puffs.

title: tomato, feta and onion salad
directions: Marinate overnight and serve.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, to creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture.
Mix well. Pour batter into an ungreased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 to 90 minutes.

title: tuna salad veronique
directions: Combine mayonnaise with vinegar and seasonings.
Chill all ingredients.
When ready to serve, tear greens into bite-size pieces and place in bowl.
Drain tuna and break into chunks over lettuce.
Add grapes and dressing and toss lightly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs light and foamy. Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix lightly but well. Add flour mixture. Mix well. Add nuts. Divide batter into 2 well greased loaf pans. Bake in 325 degree oven for 1 hr. or until done. Freezes well.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Shell eggs and cut in half.
Remove the yolk carefully and mash yolks with fork.
Add the next 4 ingredients and mix until smooth and fluffy.
Spoon the yolk mixture into egg whites.
Top each half with sprinkle of paprika.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in a lightly greased pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave southern pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans in deep three quart casserole, mix well.
Microwave on high 4 1/2 minutes, stir.
Stir in pecans and microwave for 6 1/2 minutes; stirring at 3 minutes. Let cool for 1-2 minutes.
Stir until mixture thickens; about 3-5 minutes.
Spoon out onto wax paper or aluminum foil.
Makes approximately 45 pralines.

title: banana nuggets
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add bananas.
Add sifted dry ingredients and lastly add quick oats.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese yogurt dip
directions: With electric mixer, whip the cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in yogurt, garlic, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, tomato paste, hot pepper sauce and salt.
Transfer to serving bowl. Lightly mix in sliced olives.
Cover and chill overnight.
Serve with zucchini, celery, carrot sticks, whole radishes and fresh mushrooms.

title: country butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat with electric mixer. Rinse lightly one time.
Mold and serve with hot biscuits or potatoes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Beat butter and cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended; and flour and remaining ingredients, beating until blended.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Shape dough into 4 (8 inch) logs; cover and chill 8 hours.
Cut into 1/4 inch slices and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Remove to wire racks to cool.
Store in an airtight container. Yields:
10 dozen.

title: white texas cake
directions: Beat Crisco, sugar and egg whites until fluffy; add flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix 1 3/4 cups buttermilk, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Add to other mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar; add milk while beating.
Fold in whipped topping and beat. Pour into crust and freeze overnight.
Thaw at room temperature 15 minutes before serving.

title: corey james texas-style barbecue beef brisket
directions: In a mortar bowl, crush spices together until mixture achieves the consistency of salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Add each ingredient to the head lettuce you have cut into small pieces.
Seal lettuce and these ingredients with the mayonnaise at all sides.
Can keep in refrigerator up to 2 weeks. Serves 12.

title: layered salad
directions: Cut or tear lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Cut flowerets of broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces and layer over lettuce.
All other vegetables may be chopped or grated and individually layered.
You may substitute your favorite vegetables or leave out any vegetables you prefer.
After layers are completed and approximately 2 to 3 hours prior to serving, mix mayonnaise and sugar together and spread over entire mixture.
Add cheese and bacon bits just before topping of mayonnaise and sugar.

title: sicilian steak
directions: Cut steak in medium pieces; flour, salt and pepper. Fry in oil until done. Place in casserole dish; add spaghetti sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Take out of oven and add Mozzarella cheese. Bake additional 10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Cook noodles; pour over them.

title: hearty rice casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a greased 4 qt. baking dish; mix well.
Cover lightly and bake at 350 degrees for 60-70 minutes or until the rice is tender.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Slice potatoes and cook until almost tender.
Mix hamburger with beefy mushroom soup and spread in bottom of casserole dish.
Next, add potato slices and cover with cheese.
(For larger casseroles, double recipe and repeat layers.)
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: curry chicken divan
directions: Cook, bone and cut up chicken into large pieces.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Place broccoli in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Mix all the rest of ingredients except crumbs.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle crumbs over entire top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° in casserole about 30 minutes or until fully baked and bubbly.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add pineapple.
Let cool until slightly jelled, then add cottage cheese, salad dressing and whipped cream.

title: amish coffee cake
directions: Dissolve soda in coffee.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add reserved topping and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar after baking.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pan and cover with water. Cook for about 4 hours.
Season with parsley, onion, salt and pepper.

title: czech-style macaroni with cream of wheat
directions: Cook macaroni in salted boiling water according to directions on package.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Cook until tender but firm.
Do not overcook.
Meanwhile, melt 4 to 5 tablespoons of margarine or butter in skillet over medium heat. Add Cream of Wheat.
Stir constantly until Cream of Wheat browns, being careful not to let it scorch.
When macaroni is done, drain well and add to Cream of Wheat-margarine mixture.
Toss to coat macaroni with browned Cream of Wheat and serve.
Black pepper may be added, if desired.
Very tasty!
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick escalloped ham
directions: Simple dish.
Great for using up leftovers or fixing an inexpensive dish for a crowd.

title: foge fazio chicken
directions: Clean chicken.
Cut chicken breasts into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Place chicken pieces in beaten eggs and refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Coat chicken pieces in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in melted margarine.
Layer pieces in baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese and mushrooms over chicken.
Repeat layer.
Pour chicken stock over.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours (325° glass dish).
Tender and delicious!

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place deboned chicken in casserole dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and broth.
Heat and pour over chicken.
Mix margarine and milk; heat, then add flour.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° until brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: grandmother's nut cake
directions: Cream butter
and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; cream well. Alternate
flour
and
milk
(with vanilla).
Add nuts. Mix well and bake at 350° in well-greased lined tube pan until done.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Roll and mash 2 packages graham crackers.
Add melted butter and sugar and shape in bottom of pie plate and along sides.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.

title: green beans and hamburger
directions: Brown beef and onion. Stir in garlic, water, soy sauce and molasses.
Heat to boiling. Add green beans and rice.
Simmer 15 minutes. Blend cornstarch with 1/4 cup water.
Stir gradually into meat ingredients. Cook until thickened.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Fry bacon until done but not crisp. Spray Teflon muffin tin with nonstick spray.
Cover bottom of each muffin receptacle with sauteed bread crumbs. Add spoonful of grated cheese. Circle slice of bacon inside each receptacle.
You can do this the night before having guests for brunch.

title: heavenly hash jello salad
directions: Make Jell-O according to directions.
Use 1/2 mixture and drain peaches well.
Let set until slightly firm.
Take other half of Jell-O and beat until fluffy.
Beat cottage cheese and Cool Whip until well mixed.
Fold into whipped Jell-O and layer on top of peach mixture.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese with mixer until well blended. Stir in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate about 3 hours. Top with fresh fruit or pie filling

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix cereal, nuts, pretzels, and raisins (if you have to have them) in a big bowl (dish pan will be best). Melt choc. chips, peanut butter, and oleo together. Pour over cereal mix until everything us well covered. Pour powdered sugar into a brown paper bag and dump cereal mix into the bag. Shake to mix well. Lay out flat to dry. ENJOY! Makes alot.

title: french onion dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and soup mix. Cover and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables or potato chips. Garnish, if desired.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, blending well. Stir in remaining ingredients and divide into 2 balls. Chill for about 2 hours. Roll balls in chopped pecans.

title: kentucky lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and melted margarine.
Beat well. Add pinch of salt.
Add lemon juice and lemon rind.
Beat until mixed well.
Put the mixture in a 9-inch uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 275° for about 50 minutes or until brown.
Let cool before serving.

title: mocha truffles
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl or double boiler, melt chocolate chips.
Add cream cheese, coffee and water; mix well.
Chill until firm enough to shape.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours or until firm.

title: garlic buttered green beans
directions: Cook green beans in water to cover until tender.

title: noodles
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add salt, baking powder and milk. Add flour until stiff.
Roll out on floured board until paper thin.
Let dry 1/2 hour.
Cut into strips.

title: turketti
directions: Cook spaghetti in salt water until soft; drain.
Combine all the ingredients and pour into a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peach bellinis
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well.
Let stand at room temperature 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Transfer peach mixture to container of an electric blender; process on medium speed 1 minute.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then take Solomon's advice in Proverbs 23:14 for making good boys.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
If using self-rising flour, omit salt and baking powder.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower and broccoli.
Slice onion and cheese.
Mix sugar and salad dressing.
Let stand about 20 minutes.
Pour over salad and sprinkle bacon across the top.

title: veg-all cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken and spinach bake
directions: Cook spinach as on package.
Drain thoroughly and spread over the bottom of a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread chicken over spinach.
Melt butter and blend in flour; add chicken soup, chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce boils and thickens.
Add lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over chicken; sprinkle with cheese and dust with paprika. Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until nice and brown.

title: pizza casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef, onions and green peppers. Drain off excess grease.
Stir in pizza sauce, mushrooms, crushed oregano and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Cook rotini according to package directions and drain well. Combine rotini with milk.
When thoroughly mixed, stir in pizza sauce mixture.
Grate cheese (2 cups).
In lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish, layer meat and sauce mixture and cheese. Repeat layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: persimmon, date and nut pudding
directions: Sift flour with sugar, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the bread crumbs.
Combine the melted butter with milk and vanilla; add to dry ingredients and mix until blended.
Stir in the persimmon pulp, dates and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Serve with lemon sauce, whipped cream or ice cream.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: aunt neva's pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together until smooth and pour into crust.
Bake for about one hour.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and mix with liquid. Add prunes and nuts, mix well. Pour into Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and 7-Up together; add food coloring. Cook until thick; let cool.
Add fresh strawberries and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: quick homemade beef stew
directions: Brown beef stew meat in oil until tender.
Add rest of vegetables and gravy and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Very good with warm rolls.

title: blake and brooke's favorite mexican casserole
directions: After browning and draining the ground beef, mix it with the soups.
Layer the bottom of a casserole dish with either the crushed Fritos or tortillas.
Then add the beef-soup mixture and finally the cheese.
Continue in this order until all ingredients are used.
Be sure to finish with the grated cheese on top.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat.
Gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Combine coconut and nuts; sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until puffed and browned.
(Filling will be soft, but will set while cooling.)
Cool at least 4 hours before cutting.

title: turtle bars
directions: Mix on high for 2 minutes the cake mix, butter and milk.
Put half cake batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Spread caramel on cake.
Sprinkle with 1 cup or desired amount of chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour on remaining cake batter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Cake will not test done.)
Cool and frost with fudge icing.

title: chocolate chip cupcakes
directions: Sift
together	flour,	baking	powder and salt.
Cream shortening with
sugar
and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating
well
after
each addition.
Mix chocolate chips with part of
the
flour
mixture
and add to creamed mixture.
Add flour alternately with milk in small amounts.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: In skillet brown meat with green peppers and onions.
Drain fat, mix in salt, chili powder, Tabasco sauce and water.
Boil 1 cup corn meal, 3 cups water and 1/2 teaspoon salt together. Spread thin layer of meal mixture in baking dish.
Spread layer of meat mixture over meal.
Continue layering and end with layer of meal mixture on top.
Spoon 2 or 3 tablespoons water on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook hamburger with garlic and salt until brown.
Stir soups into the meat.
Line bottom of a baking dish with crushed tortillas.
Alternate layers of meat, green chili strips, onion and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: simple pie
directions: Mix together the condensed milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice. Add mandarin oranges and pineapple (both drained).
Add nuts and mix well.
Pour into crusts and refrigerate.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Place butter and onion in a 1-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, in microwave on full power for 2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until tender. Stir in soup, sour cream, coriander and cumin.
Mix well and set aside.

title: savory tomato dressing
directions: Combine tomato juice, onion, Italian seasoning and gelatin in small saucepan. Let stand 5 minutes. Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes. Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in crock-pot on low for 3 to 4 hours. Stir every 30 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl; add eggs and oil. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well-greased pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Wear rubber gloves to handle jalapenos.
Combine vinegar, peppers and sugar.
Boil 4 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Add pectin and green color.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Makes 5 (6 ounce) jars.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: In a bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Spread on buns. Layer slices of ham and cheese in buns.
Wrap for freezing. Freeze.

title: chocolate meringue pie(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, salt, milk and egg yolks in a large Pyrex bowl.
Mix with a wire whip.
Microwave on High for up to 9 minutes or until cooked to desired thickness.
Stir occasionally
with wire whip to keep from lumping.
After cooking to desired thickness, add butter and stir with wire whip until butter melts.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: homesteader's beef roll-ups
directions: Let rolls rise according to package directions.
Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add all other ingredients except cheese. Flatten rolls to 5-inch circle.
Sprinkle cheese on top of dough. Add meat mixture to each circle.
Pinch together edges of dough, completely closing it around filling.
Bake, seam side down, in greased muffin pans until golden brown at 375°, about 15 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake
mix and dry gelatin.
Stir in oil, water and 2 eggs. Beat 2 minutes.
Add rest of eggs and beat 2 minutes.
Add strawberries (thawed but not mushy).
Beat 1 minute.
Pour into well-greased, floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix together in bowl and press into deep Pyrex dish.

title: raisin bread
directions: Soak raisins for 20 minutes in hot water before bread is mixed.
Drain and let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Heat milk to lukewarm.
Then add all liquids to 1/2 of flour mixture to make soft dough.
Add beaten eggs and raisins.
Stir well and add balance of flour.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead well.
Put in oiled bowl; let rise 50 minutes, then divide in half.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Bake in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan after dough has doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fried apple pie
