directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Rub in shortening; add enough milk to make stiff pastry dough.
Cook dried apples until tender.
Mash with a potato masher.
Sweeten to taste.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon (or more, if desired). Roll dough out to medium-thin thickness.
Use a saucer to cut rounds of dough.
Place dried apples on half of dough; moisten edges with water.
Fold over and seal.
Fry in a heavy skillet in a small amount of shortening over very low heat until dough is well done and delicately browned.

title: cran-apple pie
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook 1 minute longer, continuing to stir.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the cranberries; pour into a pie shell.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine and mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Drain well and serve hot.
Can be frozen, then thawed and reheated in microwave oven.

title: clam cakes
directions: Mix clam juice, egg, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper. Stir in clams and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done, then bone.
In 9 x 12-inch pan, put a layer of Doritos, then layer of chicken.
Combine melted cheese, Ro-Tel, broth and soups.
Pour over chicken and Doritos.
Crumble remaining Doritos on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and bake in Pyrex bowl at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve while warm with crackers.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Slowly cook pineapple and cornstarch until clear and pour over cake.
Beat cream cheese, eggs and sugar. Pour over pineapple and bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: bacardi rum cake - just like the island's
directions: Grease Bundt pan; sprinkle nuts over the bottom of the pan. Combine cake mix and remaining ingredients together. Mix as for cake. Pour batter over nuts and bake 1 hour in a 325° oven. Remove from oven and invert on serving plate. Prick top with fork.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in an oblong pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Layer ingredients in order listed.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Mix all together.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add last of all. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake as you would a cake.

title: egg rolls
directions: Fry hamburger until brown; drain.
Take bean sprouts (drained and rinsed) and add to meat.
Shake soy sauce over this mixture and place in each egg roll wrapper.
Fold as directed.
Heat oil in deep fryer; deep fry until light brown.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Make cornbread according to directions on box.
Crumble cornbread into bowl.
Chop onions, tomatoes and bell pepper; add to cornbread.
Mix with mayonnaise.
You may add more if it's too dry.
Crumble cooked bacon on top.

title: dilly cheese ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine butter, cheese, dill weed and garlic powder.
Separate biscuits.
Cut each in half and place 20 pieces in ungreased fluted tube pan.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture over top.
Repeat with remaining biscuits and cheese mixture.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool 1 minute; remove from pan.
Serve warm. Yields 10 servings.

title: hershey's vanilla chip fruit tart(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat butter and confectioners sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Press mixture onto bottom and up side of a 12-inch round pizza pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely.
Prepare Vanilla Filling. Spread on cooled crust.
Cover.
Chill.
Prepare Fruit Topping. Cover.
Chill assembled tart.

title: dianne's brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken in water.
When done, debone and cut into small pieces.
Reserve broth.
Brown sausage in large pot.
Add onion. As the onion and sausage cook, begin adding the whole tomatoes, corn, butter beans and potatoes.
Add 2 cups of chicken broth and the chicken, in small pieces.
Once all ingredients are in the pot, simmer for 3 to 4 hours, uncovered.
Add to your taste, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Catsup can also be added if a sweeter stew is preferred and/or as much hot sauce as desired.
More broth can also be added as the stew simmers, depending on how thick you desire the stew.

title: onion souffle
directions: Defrost onions and squeeze liquid out.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake, uncovered, in 2 qt. casserole dish for 15 minutes at 425°.
Serve with corn chips (Scoops are best for dipping), Triscuits or Melba rounds.

title: danish pastry
directions: Blend flour, butter and water into dough.
Roll into ball; divide in half.
Pat dough into strips 12 x 3 on cookie sheet.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Take excess
skin off of chicken and salt and pepper to taste. Roll
chicken
in
cornflake crumbs.
Place chicken in pan that has
been sprayed with Pam.
Cook in oven at 400° for one hour.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix and beat in blender until smooth.
This recipe equals 2 cans of milk.

title: buckeye ball candies
directions: Mix well the butter, powdered sugar, crunchy peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Melt chocolate over hot water or in microwave until melted and dip balls into chocolate with toothpick.
Put onto wax paper to cool.

title: christmas popcorn cake(no bake)
directions: Mix all ingredients excluding popcorn in a pot and stir over low heat.
When melted, mix with popcorn.
Pour into greased tube cake pan.
Let set for 3 to 4 hours and then remove for serving.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the pecans.
Shape into a ball.
Refrigerate, then roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers. Makes 20 servings.

title: pizza pie
directions: Brown and drain ground beef; mix beef, paste, water and spaghetti sauce.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: easy kibe
directions: Soak wheat salad mix in cold water for 30 minutes.
Saute with margarine, 2 onions and approximately 1/2 pound ground beef until golden brown.
Reserve this for filling.
In a food processor, mix the remaining beef, onions and drained wheat.
Add seasoning from the salad mix.
Put the mixture in a large bowl; add margarine with hands, blending well.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend lemon juice into condensed milk.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts. Spoon into pie shells.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and mix all ingredients well, except 1 cup pecans.
Place in refrigerator; let it chill.
Roll into ball and roll in 1 cup pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, bring broth, tomatoes, onion, cabbage, vegetables and seasonings to a boil.
Add macaroni and simmer 10 minutes or until tender.
Add meat and heat thoroughly. Yield:
6 servings.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix soda, raisins and water; let cool.
Add oil; cover and let set overnight.
Next day, add sugar, salt, flour and nuts.
Mix well and divide into 3 equal parts.
Place each third into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. After removing from oven, let set for 20 minutes before removing from pan and serving.

title: sweet and spicy barbecued brisket
directions: Season brisket with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Place in 3-quart shallow baking dish. Mix salsa, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce. Spread over brisket. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serve over tomatoes, cut partially open into wedges.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together gently.

title: punch
directions: In
an	enamel	pot
add
enough
hot water to dissolve sugar. Add
citric
acid.
Add	orange	juice.	Stir
until completely dissolved.
Add
pineapple juice; stir.
Divide in half
equally and put into 2 (1 gallon) containers.
Add cold water
to fill up rest of the way.
Add food color if desired. Freeze.
Add
64 ounces ginger ale per gallon frozen punch in punch	bowl.
This punch
is its own ice.
Just chop it up in ginger ale.
One gallon will serve 25 people.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in order
given, adding raw apples and nuts last to the batter.
The batter will be thick!
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: bran apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine bran and milk; let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add apples, butter and egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon into well-greased or paper-lined muffin cups, filling 1/2 full.
Bake 25 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: moody's chocolate morsel pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in eggs and butter.
Add pecans, chocolate morsels and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until golden in color.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box and allow to thicken.
Mix in 3/4 of the container of Cool Whip and the condensed milk.
Alternate pudding, bananas and wafers in large bowl.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Wash and dry chicken breast.
Combine poultry seasoning, seasoning salt, salt and pepper; rub mixture into chicken, being sure to cover all sides.
Flour, using enough flour to coat lightly.
Quickly brown in hot butter in heavy skillet.
Turn to brown evenly.
Transfer to 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir 1 tablespoon flour into drippings, brown slightly, then add water. Mix well and pour over the chicken.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Remove cover last 10 minutes to crisp crust.
Serves 8.

title: yellow jacket corn
directions: Cook bacon until crispy; drain and crumble.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon drippings in skillet.
Add corn, green pepper and onion.
Cook over high heat for 5 minutes, stirring often; stir in bacon, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into a highly greased 2-quart shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients (except tortillas).
Spread the mixture on tortillas.
Roll up tightly and place on waxed paper pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice each into 5 to 6 pieces.
Place on a platter with a bowl of picante sauce to dip these in when served.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Let cheese soften.
Peel cucumber, grate and drain well.
Mix all ingredients and spread on bread that has been cut 4 ways.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add and blend well the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 3 greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans 3/4 full.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well in very large bowl.
Store in tightly closed container.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: In a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer rice, ham, onion and broccoli.
In another bowl combine soup, cheese and milk.
Spread over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While baking, crumble bread and sauce in butter and sprinkle over casserole, then continue baking for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In a casserole dish put a layer of potatoes, hamburger meat, onion and then cheese. Then start all over with ingredients.
Put soup on top and bake about 45 minutes in oven at 400°.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Pastry:
Let cream cheese and 2 sticks butter soften at room temperature.
Blend the cream cheese and butter together.
Stir in flour.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Mix all ingredients. Strain (mixture will be very thin).
Pour into frozen pie shell and bake until done, about 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: key lime pie(diabetic)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Cool slightly. Fold in yogurt and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and chill at least 3 hours.

title: chocolate volcano
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 1/4 inch quiche pan and an 8x8 inch square pan. Prepare brownies as package directed. Pour half in each pan. Bake 20 mins. Cool. Combine cranberries, sugar and water. Bring to boil reduce heat and gently boil about 10 mins. Combine cornstarch and water in a bowl; add to saucepan whisking until thickens. Chill. Cut half the brownies in the square pan into 1/2 inch cubes and the other half reg. to enjoy later. Spoon cranberry mixture over brownie in the quiche pan. Sprinkle brownie cubes and peanuts on top. Drizzle warmed fudge sauce on top. Cut into wedges to serve.

title: rice and beans
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a medium saucepan over medium heat.
Once the sofrito melts, add next 3 ingredients (optional).
Raise the heat to high for 15 minutes.
After 15 minutes, adjust for salt, then simmer on low for 15 minutes. Serve with white rice.
Fried pork chops go real well with this combo, but it is really good by itself.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a bowl.
Add eggs, nutmeg and flour.
Beat until well mixed.
Shape into 3 rolls, 2 inches in diameter and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill for 3 hours.
Cut in 1/4 inch slices and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes, then sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Roll out Oreos.
Use half of crumbs to cover bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add enough warm water to make stiff dough.
Roll dough in balls about size of a large lemon. Roll balls with rolling pin to about 6 to 8-inches in diameter. Bake on ungreased cast-iron griddle until done.
Tortillas will be white when done, with light brown spots.
Flour tortillas may be wrapped in foil after cooking and stored in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days.
Then reheat.
Do not bake or warm over high heat.

title: christmas cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread peaches in syrup in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top in even layers.
Cut butter in thin slices and cover top completely.
Bake for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients except sour cream. Pour half the mixture into rectangular Pyrex dish.
Let congeal.
When congealed, spread sour cream over the entire portion.
Pour remaining jello mixture over sour cream. Congeal.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit and arrange in a baking dish.
Melt butter and mix it with sugar and curry powder.
Pour over fruit.
Bake uncovered at 300° for
1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Put pecans on cookie sheet.
Toast at 250° for 15 minutes until you smell them.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix chocolate, Eagle Brand and whipping cream until fluffy and increased in volume by 1/3 to 1/2 (no more than 10 minutes).
Add pecans to mixture and freeze in Tupperware.
Spoon out when ready to serve.

title: crispix chocolate drops
directions: Melt together chips (low heat on stove or microwave) until just melted.
Stir in Crispix and nuts.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper or foil lined pan.
Chill until firm.
May be stored in tightly covered container at room temperature after cooled.

title: guinataan crab
directions: Shell shrimp, devein, place in a saucepan.
Add the thin coconut milk, ginger and dilao.
Let boil until shrimp turn red.
Add coco cream, hot pepper and salt.
Just before serving, add green onions.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Blend cream cheese, egg yolk and cayenne pepper until smooth. Melt butter with lemon juice.
Pour into cream cheese mixture and blend to desired consistency.
Add garlic powder and salt to taste.
Serve over asparagus, broccoli, eggs, etc.

title: freda's corn casserole
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and pour into large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until bubbly and brown on top.

title: easy strawberry-rhubarb dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, layer all the ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: curried artichoke rice salad
directions: Combine all with cooked rice when it is cool.
Chill at least 6 hours.
Serve on lettuce garnished with cherry tomato and olives.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine egg white and water.
Mix nuts and toss in egg white to coat.
Mix sugar, spice and salt.
Toss nuts in sugar mixture to coat.
Place in single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on waxed paper.
Break up clumps.
Store in dry container.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt, sugar, oil and flour.
Mix well to soft dough.
Let rise.
When double, pour over on floured board.
Knead well.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine.

title: quick corned beef casserole
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Mix soup and milk, then pour into corned beef mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
(Can use bread crumbs.)

title: great cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs with melted margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan; bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: jogging juice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Drink 2 ounces a day.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients and shortening.
Blend with a fork until it resembles small dry grains.
Add enough water to make soft, smooth dough, not sticky.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick; cut into round shapes.
Gather scraps and reroll.
If you want drop biscuits, add more water until sticky and drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 7 to 9 biscuits.

title: sour cream pear pie
directions: Combine pears, sugar, egg, flour, sour cream, vanilla and salt.
Blend gently.
Spoon into crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle topping over pie and return to oven for 30 more minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix together chicken, spaghetti, peas and soup in casserole dish.
Season with salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese. Top with bread crumbs or Ritz crackers (crushed).
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: lemon sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat the sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients, then ReaLemon brand; mix well.
Chill 2 hours.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Roll in additional sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet; flatten.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: three bean soup
directions: Cook each pound of beans separately. Brown hamburger and onion together and drain. Combine all ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; add rice and stir until golden brown.
Add chopped onion and saute until onion turns color (clear-translucent).
Add chicken stock and tomato paste.
Simmer, covered, until rice is tender for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cantonese-style egg foo yong
directions: Mix eggs, meat, celery, mushrooms, bamboo shoots, onions, salt, m.s.g. and pepper in large bowl; do not beat.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in deep skillet, Dutch oven or wok over medium heat.
Spoon 1/4 of the egg mixture into oil carefully.
Cook until edges are brown; turn gently.
Brown on other side.
Remove to plate.
Fry remaining 3 portions in same manner, adding additional oil if needed.
Serve hot, plain or with sauce.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: 14 karat gold salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add juice, vinegar and milk. In mixer or blender, add cream cheese and blend until smooth.
Add carrots and pineapple. Pour into prepared 2-quart mold.
Chill until set.

title: banana split crumb cake
directions: Mix oleo, 1/2 cup of sugar and graham cracker crumbs and place in bottom of pan (oblong sheet cake pan).
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: jello pie
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sugar and Jell-O in saucepan; bring to a boil.
After mixture has cooled, add milk that has been chilled and whipped.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: glazed cinnamon raisin biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Lightly grease a baking sheet. Sift together the flour, cinnamon, and brown sugar. Stir in raisins.

With electric mixer on low speed, gradually add the whipping cream, beating only until mixture begins to form a dough. Flours differ in the amount of liquid needed to form a dough, so it might be necessary to add just a little more whipping cream but only add about a tablespoon at a time.
Drop from a tablespoon into mounds on baking sheet, spacing the biscuits about 2 inches apart. Bake for about 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from baking sheet to a rack to cool.
While biscuits are cooling, mix together the confectioners sugar and water or milk. Beat until it becomes a smooth, pourable mixture.
Drizzle the glaze over the cooled cinnamon biscuits.

title: old fashion chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients; toss gently.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Spoon into a serving dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Garnish with parsley and cherry tomatoes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cool whip delight
directions: Put milk in a bowl; dip cookies in milk and put in long pan or dish.
Cover with layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers until all has been used.
Sprinkle with coconut and chill for several hours.

title: turkey goulash
directions: Brown turkey in a nonstick skillet with seasonings.
Add tomatoes, pepper, onion, sweetener and mushrooms with juice. Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni and continue boiling, uncovered, until juice is absorbed and macaroni is tender (approximately 20 minutes).

title: molasses peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrups.
Boil to 290°.
Remove from heat and add soda and peanuts.
Quickly pour in greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: josh's apple and banana salad
directions: Have your Mom do the following:
Peel banana and apples.
Cut into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Serves one hungry kid.

title: e - z fudge
directions: Melt the chips with the sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in vanilla, salt and nuts.
Take off heat and add marshmallows.
Stir enough to make white streaks in fudge when poured into buttered dish.
Chill and set.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds of fudge.

title: macadamia nut cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix in nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: cocoon cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Shape in a half moon.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Roll in sifted powdered sugar; lay on wax paper until cool.

title: potato, pepper and kielbasa casserole
directions: Core and seed peppers; cut in 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in large bowl.
Cut onions in thin wedges; add to bowl.
Halve potatoes;
add
to
bowl.
Peel casing from kielbasa if necessary. Cut
into 1/2-inch thick slices; add to bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and
pepper;
toss
with
oil.
Transfer mixture to shallow 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil.
Bake
35 minutes.
Stir in cream, cover and bake 10 minutes more until bubbly and oil and cream have come together.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Bake in 400° oven for 55 minutes.

title: grilled chicken marinade
directions: Mix ingredients.
Marinade will be plenty for 2 to 3 pounds of chicken.
Marinate chicken for several hours.
Brush remainder of marinade over chicken while cooking.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together chicken, soup and Veg-All.
Pour into pie crust. Dot with butter.
Top with crust.
Brush with milk and bake at 325° until done.

title: shrimp and scallops in white sauce
directions: Saute shrimp and scallops in 1 tablespoon butter until lightly cooked, about 5 minutes. In separate skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter; add flour, thyme, garlic powder, salt and pepper, stirring until smooth. Gradually add milk and parmesan cheese. Stir until bubbly and thickens. Stir in shrimp and scallops; heat for 5 more minutes on low. Serve over hot angel hair pasta, with salad and garlic cheese toast.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread all sides of chicken with mustard.
Coat with bread
crumbs.
Place
on a foil-lined and greased baking pan.
Dot
with
butter.
Bake until chicken is cooked through and bread
crumbs are golden, about 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving. Serve with sliced apples.

title: miniature pizzas
directions: Melt cheese; add sausage, catsup, garlic, onion and oregano. Spread on party rye.
This is enough for approximately 1 1/2 loaves.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, put in plastic bags.
Keep frozen.
Bake frozen for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pie
directions: Sift flour and salt together in a 9-inch pie plate.
Measure cold milk and oil together in measuring cup.
Do not stir.
Add all at once to flour.
Stir lightly with fork until all ingredients are blended.
Reserve about 1 cup of mixture for topping.
Shape crust by pulling and tamping dough with your fingers in pan.
Smooth bottom of pie with smooth glass.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add ground cinnamon and salt to flour mixture. Mix in
egg
mixture.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put
in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: blessing pie
directions: Pat the crushed gingersnaps and butter into a 9-inch pie pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 300°.
Mix the whipped cream, pistachio pudding and pineapple together.
Pour into cooled crust.
Top the pie with almonds and coconut.
Deliver to someone special with your love and a blessing card.

title: phillip's favorite enchiladas
directions: Cook ground beef and season to taste.
Fill 6 to 8 flour tortillas with beef and put 2 to 3 tablespoons of cheese in it, too.
Roll.
Top with soups and Ro-Tel.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press in greased cake pan (press evenly).

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Add all ingredients and toss.
No need to measure.
Add amount depending on family taste of each.
Serve either warm or chilled.

title: waffles
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in hot waffle iron until brown.
Serve with syrup and butter.

title: peggy garner's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer 20 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage and bring to boil.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Remove leaves as they cook; cool and drain.
Mix hamburger, rice and seasonings.
Drop a tablespoon of mixture on stem end of each cabbage leaf.
Roll up.
Place in casserole.
Pour tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fajitas
directions: Trim fat from beef.
Prick beef with fork in several places. Mix 1/4 cup oil, wine, sugar, oregano, chili powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper in ungreased square baking dish.
Place beef in dish, turning once to coat both sides.
Cover and refrigerate, turning beef occasionally at least 8 hours but no longer than 24 hours.
Wrap tortillas in aluminum foil and heat in a 325° oven until warm, about 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; keep tortillas wrapped.
Remove beef from marinade; reserve marinade. Set oven control to broil or 550°.

title: thomas' favorite spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare spaghetti noodles as usual. Place noodles in a casserole dish and layer with chopped Velveeta cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Heat in oven for 10 minutes.
Serve piping hot.

title: baked apple dumplings
directions: Peel and chop apples; set aside.
Roll biscuits out thin, one at a time.
Fill with apples and stretch dough over apples and seal edges.
Place in oblong pan.
Combine 7-Up, margarine, sugar and cinnamon.
Let come to a boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over dumplings and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute first three ingredients in oil.
Add gravy mix dissolved in chicken broth or water.
Add mushrooms, Ro-Tel tomatoes, cheese and chicken.
Stir until warm and cheese is melted.
Layer mixture with spaghetti in Pyrex dish that is sprayed with Pam.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato balls(yields 6 servings)
directions: Mash potatoes thoroughly.
Add egg yolk, salt, cinnamon and butter, mixing well.
Mold potato mixture around marshmallows, forming 6 balls with a marshmallow in the center of each.
Beat egg white until foamy.
Roll balls in egg white, then in corn flakes.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Bake until golden brown.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix 1 package of Royal lemon pie filling with 1/2 cup sugar. Gradually stir in 2 1/4 cups water and slightly beaten egg yolks. Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture comes to a boil. Pour into a cooled baked pie shell.

title: lemon-parsley turnips
directions: Cook turnips until tender.
Drain well.
Add butter, parsley, lemon juice and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir gently to coat.

title: ham and rice bake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and pour into an oblong, lightly greased baking dish.
Combine corn flakes and melted margarine and spread over casserole mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and melted butter or margarine.
Spread in a 9-inch pie plate.
Press mixture onto bottom and sides of pie plate.
Refrigerate.

title: homemade chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except for boiling water until well blended.
Mix with electric mixer for 3 minutes more.
Add boiling water.
Mix another minute.
Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling water about 12 minutes. Drain, rinse and cover with cold water.
Heat vegetable oil in saucepan.
Add onion, carrots and garlic.
Saute until carrots are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and spices. Bring to a simmer.
Beat eggs and blend in cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and vegetables.

title: chili con queso
directions: Brown beef; drain and add to pot.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Add crushed tomatoes and all spices to pot.
Add tomato paste.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add kidney beans; heat thoroughly. Serve in ovenproof crock-pot.
Top with Cheddar cheese, then brown under broiler.

title: low calorie orange cheesecake
directions: Mix first two ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes in spring-form pan or glass dish.
Sprinkle gelatin over orange juice and heat.
Add cheeses, Cool Whip and sweetener.
Pour into crust.
Place fruit on top.
Chill.

title: cheddar ham chowder
directions: In large saucepan, bring water, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 8 to 10 minutes, or until veggies are just tender.
Remove from heat; do not drain.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut partially frozen cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange cookie slices, slightly overlapping, on 13-inch pizza pan.
Press edges to seal.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes. Add cooked hamburger.
Add 1/2 cheese and rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir cheese until melts.
Then add rice and meat.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle on rest of cheese.
Bake in 325° oven about 15 or 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: spinach ricotta pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place spinach and onion in small saucepan. Cover and cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Beat cheeses and seasonings in a small bowl at medium speed with mixer until well blended.
Stir in spinach mixture. Spread into a 9-inch pie plate. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with rye crackers or bagel chips. Makes 12 servings.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown sausage and bacon in different pans.
Mix onion with sausage.
Drain fat.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Cover and cook in slow cooker or oven until heated through.
Bake in a 325° oven for at least 1 hour.

title: crab melts
directions: Mix all ingredients except crabmeat, then fold in crabmeat. Spread on top of 1/4 pieces of English muffins.
Broil until browned.
Serve warm.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until soft and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and cream alternately until right consistency.
Put in cold oven.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven door until after 1 hour.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in small muffin tins at 350° for 20 minutes if freezing, or 30 minutes if eaten at once.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apple pie filling in a greased 13 x 9-inch pie pan. Pour on dry cake mix.
Place butter in squares on top of cake mix. Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fluffy french toast
directions: Beat egg white with sugar until stiff. Set aside. Beat
egg yolk; add flour, milk, salt and baking powder. Fold in egg white. Dip bread in batter and fry in 1/2 to 1-inch hot oil. Serve with powdered sugar or syrup. Serves 4.

title: mrs. sullivan's 5 pounds of fudge
directions: Combine butter, canned milk and sugar in a large, heavy saucepan or Dutch oven.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a boil; cover and boil 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Add the three kinds of chocolate, one at a time, and stir until each is melted. Add vanilla and nuts; blend.
Pour into buttered 10 x 15-inch pan and let stand until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Whole pecan halves may be pressed into the tops of the squares, if you wish.

title: easy noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Set aside.
Combine soup, milk and tuna or chicken. Add noodles.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; make white sauce with cornstarch and milk.
Mix cooked macaroni, cheese, ham, tomatoes and juice together.
Pour white sauce over top.
Fold in.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil water; add jello and cranberry sauce. Mix until jello dissolves. Add orange juice, pineapple and pecans.
Pour in mold; refrigerate until jelled.

title: summer salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Tear lettuce into small pieces.
Chop up green onions.
Mix all in a large bowl.

title: cheeseburger loaves
directions: Crush cereal.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Add egg, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Add ground beef.
Mix only until combined.
Shape into 6 loaves, about 4 inches long.
Place in single layer in shallow baking pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top each loaf with 1/2 cheese slice.
Return to oven.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: sour cream twists
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water.
Combine flour, margarine, sour cream, eggs, salt and vanilla in a large bowl.
Stir in dissolved yeast.
Beat until smooth.
Cover with foil or plastic. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or up to two days.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle some on board.
Roll dough in rectangle 15 x 18-inches. Turn so both sides are coated.
Fold over 3 times, like a letter, using cinnamon and sugar.
Roll into rectangle 1/4-inch thick again using all the sugar.
Cut into 1 x 4-inch strips.
Twist and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; dry and chop fine.
Combine.
Set in refrigerator.
Best made day before serving.

title: mounds balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Set out 20 minutes.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and wax.
Dip. Set on wax paper.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon flour and salt; dredge meat in mixture. Heat skillet; add 2 tablespoons butter.
When melted, add meat and brown quickly, flipping meat to turn all sides.
Add the mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes until onions is barely tender.
Remove meat and mushrooms from skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to pan drippings.
When melted, blend in 3 tablespoons flour and tomato paste.
Now slowly pour in the beef stock and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Return meat to the skillet; stir in the sour cream and sherry. Heat briefly.
Serve with hot rice.

title: tomato-onion-zucchini casserole
directions: Scrub zucchini and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Peel and quarter tomatoes.
Peel and slice onions.
Saute zucchini and onion in butter until wilted, then add tomatoes and saute about 2 minutes more.
Add seasoning and transfer all into buttered casserole. Cover with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Combine white crabmeat, onion, bell pepper, toast, salt and pepper.
Mix together.
Put white side of flounder on pan. Put stuffing on fillet.
Put
black
side of fish on top.
Pat with butter.
Salt and
pepper
to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can add shrimp to stuffing.

title: granny cake
directions: Combine and let come to a boil. Simmer a few minutes.
Pour over cake when removed from oven.

title: basic chinese marinade
directions: Use for fish, meat or fowl.
Marinate the meat anywhere from 15 minutes to 1 hour, then cook the meat.

title: holiday four-layer dessert
directions: Cream
together; pat out in a 9 x 13-inch pan.	Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: banana cake
directions: If ingredients are room temperature, they may all be put into the bowl at once and mixed.
If not, use the usual procedure for baking a cake.
Bake at 350° in two 8-inch layers or a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan for 35 minutes or until done.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in covered container.
Pour La Choy sweet and sour sauce over chicken.
Marinate chicken for 24 hours, turning over in container every few hours.
Remove chicken and sprinkle with 1 package of Shake 'n Bake.
Add salt, pepper and garlic. Place in baking pan.
For crispier chicken, you can place chicken on a rack over the baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: reese cups
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Add sugar until the consistency to form into balls the size of walnuts.
Add vanilla; mix thoroughly with hands.
Melt chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and remove by using toothpicks. Place on wax paper.
Makes 125 pieces.
Can freeze.
Easy, fun and wonderful!

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together the liquid ingredients; stir in Bran.
Mix dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Pour into muffin tins, either greased or lined with paper liners.
Fill tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Store remaining batter, covered, in fridge up to 4 weeks.
Stir well before using.

title: lo mein
directions: Cook vermicelli; drain and rinse.
Add onion soup mix, oil and soy sauce.
Mix until onion soup mix is dissolved.
Add all other ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: In medium mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually add lemon pie filling, beating well after each addition. Pour into graham cracker crumb crust.
Chill 2 hours or until set. Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 9.

title: marinade for meats
directions: Makes 2 cups.
Enough for 5 pounds meat.

title: nine layer salad
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients in a casserole dish.
Drain peas and add.
Spread the mayonnaise over the peas and sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Add cheese and top with bacon.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese; pour into baking dish. Bake at 400° for one hour.
Remove from oven; top with cheese. Return to oven and allow cheese to brown.
(I add one small can tomato paste for more taste.)
Simple to make and is a very tasty dish.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions. Use 3 round pans or 2 round pans and split cake into 4 layers.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: For less sweet pie, eliminate sugar.

title: stir-fry sausage with boiled rice
directions: Boil 2 cups of rice separately.
In a separate pan on medium heat, place sliced sausages.
After removing sausage, let sit in a bowl.
Then add 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil.
Add Adobo seasonings, garlic powder, black pepper and salt to oil.
Stir spices together.
Add the onions, green peppers and tomato slices. Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add 6 ounces tomato sauce; if desired more sauce.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, then add water.
Cook until thickened.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Mound strawberries in pie crusts.
Pour Jell-O over and chill.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Serves 12.

title: excellent squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade dog shampoo
directions: Measure all ingredients into a quart container that has a lid. Fill with water.
Store until needed.
For a gallon, multiply each item by four.

title: spinach stuffed pasta shells
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl until well blended.
Fill each shell with heaping tablespoonful of spinach mixture and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes until thoroughly heated.

title: bean and rice enchilada casserole
directions: In skillet brown ground beef and onion, for 5 minutes. Add green chilies at the end of cooking period. Drain.

title: guava shake
directions: Mix with blender or rotary beater.
Serves 18.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Brown sausage with all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Add to bread crumbs.
Moisten with warm water until "sticky" mixture. Stuff a 15 to 19-pound turkey.
Extra dressing may be cooked in covered buttered casserole for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.
Good with chips or crackers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine, brown sugar, granulated sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Peel peaches and cut into halves.
Place in pastry shell, cut side up.
Mix sugar, melted butter and beaten eggs.
Pour over the peaches and bake in 425° oven for 30 minutes.

title: acorn squash
directions: Bake until soft at 375°, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cut in half. Remove seeds.
Scoop out insides.
Leave the half shells intact. In the blender or mixing bowl, add the brown sugar, butter, salt and orange juice.
Whip until smooth and creamy.
Spoon into the acorn squash shells and sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired. Serves 4.

title: italian cream of wheat cakes
directions: Combine the milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; slowly add the Cream of Wheat, stirring constantly.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, until the Cream of Wheat thickens.
Remove from heat; quickly stir in beaten egg yolks, then the lemon rind and almond extract.

title: 5 day sun dill pickles
directions: Put 2 large cloves of garlic and 1 tablespoon dill seed in bottom of each quart jar.
Pack cucumbers in jars.
Mix turmeric, vinegar, alum, water and salt together and stir well.
Pour over cucumbers in jars and seal tightly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil and zucchini; blend.
Add remaining ingredients to zucchini mixture.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 loaves.

title: sour cream chili bake
directions: Cook beef
and onion; drain.
Add beans, sauce, seasoning and 1/4 cup cheese.
Begin with 2 1/2 cups chips on bottom of pan; cover
with
chili.
Bake
at
for
minutes. Spread sour cream over chili; add balance of chips and cheese. Bake 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pink panther salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator and cook on the grill.

title: special cinnamon rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water. Add next seven ingredients; mix well but, do not knead. Place in a greased bowl; cover and let stand in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour. Sprinkle with a little flour, punch down and turn onto a lightly floured board; divide in half. Roll out each half into a 12 x 8 inch rectangle; brush with margarine.

title: hanky panky (hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Fry together sausage and ground beef.
Drain.
Add Velveeta, oregano, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir until melted.
Spread on cocktail rye bread.
Freeze on cookie sheets. Place in plastic bags to store when frozen.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Melt oleo and cheese and pour over cooked carrots.
Crush crackers and mix with 3 tablespoons of melted oleo.
Put on top of carrots and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix in 2-quart casserole and bake in oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour; stir once.
Bake in microwave for 10 minutes on High; change to 50% heat and cook 25 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Put margarine in 3-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High 45 to 60 seconds, until melted.
Mix in seasoning. Add nuts and stir to coat.
Microwave on High 7 to 9 minutes or until margarine is absorbed. Stir a couple of times during the 7 to 9 minutes. Spread on paper towels on baking sheet.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: strawberry delights
directions: Combine milk, pecans and coconut in large bowl.
Add 2 packages jello (dry).
Stir thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight. Form into small balls.
Roll in remaining jello.

title: chicken-brown rice bake
directions: Saute onion in oil until crisp-tender.
Add curry powder and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add chicken broth; bring mixture to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in rice.
Cover and cook over low heat 50 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Spoon into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pizza puffs
directions: Cut biscuits in half; flatten a bit.
In center of each half, place 1/4-inch cube of cheese and 1/4 teaspoon tomato sauce.
Add a spritz of oregano.
Fold and crimp edges with a fork.
Fry in oil until golden; drain.
May be frozen.
If frozen, put on cookie sheet in 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: hazelnut tart
directions: Toss the nuts with chocolate and flour.
Set aside.
In bowl of an electric mixer, beat brown sugar and butter until very smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until combined.
Beat in corn syrup, molasses, liqueur and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in nut mixture. Pour into crust and bake in a 325° oven until deep golden, about 20 minutes.
Tent tart with foil supporting foil on either side of dish with an empty tin can.
Bake until edges are set, but center still jiggles when shaken, about 40 minutes more. Let cool on rack, then chill at least four hours to firm. Serves 12.

title: ulysses
directions: Mix.
Try figure this bloomin' one out!

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well and fold in the mandarin oranges.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate filling(rosa lee linder's recipe)
directions: Mix ingredients and boil 5 to 7 minutes.
Beat until ready to spread.
Cover cake layers.

title: peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
Arrange peach halves on bottom.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Cream butter and lemon extract until soft.
Add sugar gradually until creamy.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in dry ingredients until smooth and spoon batter over peaches. Sprinkle top of batter with mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: gretta's cornbread
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, cans of corn and sour cream.
Add cornbread mix and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: jiffy popcorn balls
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add the jello; stir until dissolved.
Pour over popped popcorn.
Mix with hands; form into balls.

title: cream cheese shortbread cookies
directions: Beat butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour. Roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into favorite shapes and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with 10x sugar mixed with small amount of milk to make icing.

title: paella
directions: Heat olive oil and brown chicken pieces on all sides. Sprinkle chicken with salt and remove from pan.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Add rice and saute until rice is golden.
Add saffron, chicken and hot water.
Cook about fifteen minutes.
Add the shrimp, peas, mussels and pimento.
Cook another fifteen minutes.
After that, let it set in pan fifteen minutes before serving.
Serves 6 people.
Buem Apetite!

title: potato pot pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix bread crumbs and milk.
Combine with eggs and seasonings.
Fold in ground beef and onion.
Careful not to mix too much.
Pour into quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Put 2 cups Cheddar cheese on top of meat dish.
Add large amount of mashed potatoes on top of cheese.
Add 1 cup Cheddar cheese on top of potatoes.
Put in broiler oven until cheese melts and edges are golden brown.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Blend soup, sour cream and milk.
Pour over potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle cheese, then melted butter over that.
Top with chips.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole for 1 hour at 370°.

title: sausage, egg, mushroom and cheese casserole
directions: Place croutons on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch prepared pan.
Top with cheese and sausage.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard.
Add mushrooms and soup.
Pour mixture over ingredients in pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Let set 5 minutes and cut.
Serves 6.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: cheesy-artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and mash well.
Mix everything in together and cook for 8 minutes in the microwave.
Serve with crackers.
Oh so yummy!

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Place
chicken breasts in a large container with cover. Mix remaining
ingredients
for marinade.
Pour over chicken. Turn chicken; cover and refrigerate 24 hours, turning several times. Cook
over	hot
coals, turning and basting at 8 to 10 minutes intervals for approximately 30 minutes or until done. Delicious.

title: blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter oblong pan.
Cream butter and brown sugar until fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in the vanilla.
Add flour and salt, beat until well mixed.
Fold in walnuts, then chocolate pieces.
Pour batter into pan and smooth the top.
Bake in center of oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Cool in pan before cutting into 2-inch squares.

title: light brownie pudding
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add milk, salad oil and vanilla, mixing until smooth.
Add chopped nuts and pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
(A nonstick pan or one coated with nonstick cooking spray may be used.)
Mix together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over entire batter.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: country peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly and add sugar, vanilla and evaporated milk.
Add fruit, mixing well.
Pour into ice cream freezer can and fill to line with whole milk.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.

title: chocolate-oatmeal-peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and bring to a boil over low heat.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Stir only 1 or 2 times while boiling. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon on waxed paper or foil.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream the cheese; add Cheddar cheese and all other ingredients except parsley flakes.
Fold in parsley flakes.
Chill and mold into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch spectacular
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans for pie crust.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch
pan
and
bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool. Cream
powdered sugar and cream cheese together and fold in
half of Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Beat together pudding mix and
milk
for
or 3 minutes.
Stir in vanilla. Spread
over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over butterscotch
layer.
Refrigerate
or 3 hours or overnight.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in pan until cheese melts, slowly. Warm tortillas, one at a time, in dry skillet.
Fill with 2 tablespoons sauce.
Roll and place seam down in 9 x 13-inch pan (spray pan with Pam and put a little sauce in bottom first). Spoon remaining sauce over enchiladas and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In baking dish, combine crushed pineapple, low-fat Russian dressing, chopped onion and poppy seed.
Place chicken in pineapple mixture.
Spoon mixture over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted water; drain well.
Keep hot.
Saute garlic lightly in butter in a large frying pan.
Stir in parsley, mushrooms and liquid, clams and juice and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Season with salt, if needed. Pile spaghetti into a large bowl; spoon hot sauce over and serve. You may top with 6 scrubbed and steamed littleneck clams (left in shell).

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and vanilla alternately with flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for one hour and 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: After measuring flour, sift it 4 or 5 times.
Cream margarine, butter and cream cheese together until fluffy.
Add sugar; mix on high speed until fluffy.
Add eggs, alternately with flour.
Mix well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a well greased tube pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Do not open door and peek.

title: grandmother's 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk and extract.
Bake in greased loaf
pan at 350° to 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or in 2 greased cake pans at 375° about 25 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg yellows.
Add melted chocolate. Mix soda in milk.
Then add milk and flour.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, salt and egg whites.
Pour into three 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° until done.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over Nabisco bran and set aside. Cream sugar, Crisco, eggs, buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Add bran mixture and raisins last.
Place in refrigerator.
Will keep 2 months.
Makes 60 muffins.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.
Bake as you want them.
Makes gallon jar.
Keep covered. Don't stir after you put in refrigerator.
Just dip out into muffin tins.

title: german cucumber salad
directions: Cover cucumbers and onion with vinegar, dill weed and sugar and marinate for 2 or 3 hours in fridge.
Pour off vinegar; drain on paper towels.

title: mexican chicken roll-ups
directions: Use number of chicken breasts for the number of people.
Pound chicken breasts, place 1/2 to 1 whole green chile in center, add cheese (sliced or grated) and cilantro.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Beat egg. Mix flour, cornmeal and 1/2 package taco seasoning.
Dip chicken in egg and then roll in flour mixture. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together.
Layer on platter:
Bean dip, sour cream mixture, green onions, olives, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk together in double boiler.
Set aside.
Mix together first 4 ingredients, it will be fairly dry.
Press half of mixture into bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over.
Pour caramel mixture over chips.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Refrigerate and cut.

title: hot spiced percolator punch
directions: Pour juice and water into bottom part of 8-cup percolator. Place other ingredients in basket top.
Allow to perk.
Serve hot.

title: * beef patties *
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and shape into patties; brown.
In an ovenproof pan, mix the soup, gravy mix and 1/2 can water.
Add the thoroughly cooked patties and bake in slow oven 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.

title: easy pickles
directions: Drain pickles.
Cut in slices.
Fill jar halfway with pickle slices.
Put in 2 cups sugar and 2 tablespoons tarragon vinegar. Fill jar with remainder of pickles.
Shake well every time you go by refrigerator.

title: never fail biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour with a fork.
Add buttermilk. Blend together just until moistened.
(DO NOT OVERBEAT.)
Pat out on floured cloth; cut into 2-inch rounds.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: oven baked apple pancake
directions: Combine mix, water, eggs and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Saute apples in butter until soft.
Pour apples into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle nuts over apples.
Pour pancake batter over apples and nuts.
Combine cinnamon and the remaining sugar; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes or until pancake is puffed and sugar is melted.

title: italian sausage
directions: Cut
pork
into
cubes.
Mix salt, black pepper and red pepper together.
In
large pan mix thoroughly the seasonings and
meat together.
Add
fennel seed to meat mixture and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Clean pork casing by rinsing in warm
water, then
let
water run through the casing to clean inside.
Grind meat with chilli plate first, then with sausage plate
to
stuff sausage in casing.
Cook sausage in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: sauce for fruit or pound cake
directions: Put brown sugar and butter in a small pot and cook until bubbling.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and sour cream.

title: broccoli casserole with almonds
directions: Arrange broccoli in buttered casserole.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese.
Spoon over broccoli; top with crackers and nuts.
Bake, uncovered, in 1 1/2-quart casserole for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp alfredo for two
directions: In a saucepan, combine water, milk and margarine.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in noodle mix.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in zucchini.
Cook over medium heat about 3 minutes more or until noodles are tender.
Do not boil.
Gently stir in drained shrimp or fresh shrimp.
Heat through.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Add picante sauce.
Top with finely shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and shredded cheese.

title: bran muffins
directions: *Plus more if you don't use Bran Buds.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all together and put potato chips on the top of the macaroni.
Put in oven about 5 minutes to get golden brown.

title: curry turnovers
directions: Cut end from unsplit frankfurter roll.
With fork, hollow out enough center to hold a frankfurter.
Spread hollow generously with mustard.
Insert frankfurter.
Wrap in wax paper and chill. Cut into slices.
Dot each slice with a bit of pickle relish.

title: cheese cake tarts
directions: Cream 1 cup of sugar and cream cheese.
Add 2 teaspoons of vanilla and eggs and mix until creamy.
Pour into muffin pan lined with aluminum type cupcake papers.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°. Remove and cool 5 minutes.

title: iron skillet cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Pour oil into a skillet.
Mix cornmeal, eggs, buttermilk and mayonnaise and pour into skillet.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: king salad
directions: Mix above ingredients and either refrigerate or freeze, good either way.

title: fluffy banana cake
directions: Grease 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Sprinkle with flour, shaking out excess.
Sift flour once before measuring.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put into small bowl the bananas.
Beat on medium speed until mashed.
Measure out 1 cup.
Sift the flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Put into large bowl the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on high speed for 1 1/2 minutes, scraping bowl while beating.
Stop mixer.
Add buttermilk or sour milk.
Add sifted flour mixture alternately with mashed banana while beating on medium speed.
Scrape bowl while beating and beat only enough to blend, about 2 minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a shallow dish. Dip fish in milk and dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Beat cake mix, pudding mix, milk and eggs together.
Pour into 3 oiled and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Spread frosting between layers.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Brown sausage and hamburg.
Add Velveeta cheese until melted. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Spoon onto party rye (can be frozen and placed in Ziploc bags).
Heat in 350° oven until melted slightly on top (bubbly).

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix by hand.
Chill and shape in balls and dip in chocolate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Cool some.
Pour 1 cup or more if desired sliced strawberries in baked pie crust.
Pour thickened part over strawberries.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Makes 1 pie.
Can be used with fresh peaches or berries.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix 1 cup chopped nuts with all other ingredients.
Save 1 cup to roll cheese ball.
Makes 3 cheese balls.
(These freeze well.)

title: ralph's favorite hamburger balls and gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and shape into balls.
Brown in skillet in a little lard.
Take meatballs up and put in bowl.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: While spaghetti is cooking, saute green peppers and onion in 2 tablespoons of butter.
When onions and pepper are tender, combine with all other ingredients except cheese.
Put in well-greased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Just before taking out of oven, spread cheese over top and let stay in oven until melted.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat after each one.
Add buttermilk, soda and flour.
Add 1/2 candy that has been cut in thin slices, also raisins, pecans and coconut that have been dredged with flour.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done when tested with toothpick.

title: elegant chicken ala king
directions: Cook green pepper and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter until tender, but not brown.
Push vegetables to one side and blend salt and flour in butter; stir in cream.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Add chicken and heat, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, in small bowl, blend egg yolks, paprika and 4 tablespoons of softened butter.
Set aside.
To chicken mixture, add sherry, lemon juice and onion juice.
Have chicken bubbling, then add yolk mixture all at once, stirring until blended.
Immediately remove from heat.
Stir in pimento; serve at once over toast or in puffy pastry shells.

title: chili
directions: Cook 1 hour.
Add 2 cans of kidney beans; mash 1 of them. Cook another hour.
Real good.

title: company chicken(serves 6)
directions: Cook noodles, celery, onion and green pepper together until tender.
Drain.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Turn into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: texas tumbleweeds
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter chips in glass container in microwave until melted (1 minute on High, stir, then another minute and stir until melted).
Stir in peanuts and shoestring potatoes.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie shet.
Refrigerate until set.
These can be frozen until ready to use.

title: one-dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, then ham and onion powder in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix baking mix and milk.
Pour over (evenly) soup mix. Bake 27 to 30 minutes.
Let stand at least 5 minutes.
Pie crust can be substituted for Bisquick.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown rice in small amount of oil.
Add enough water to cover rice.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
Cook until rice is done.

title: creamed dried beef on toast
directions: Cook dried beef in butter until edges frizzle.
Push meat to one side; blend flour into butter.
Add milk all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly, gradually incorporating dried beef.
Add worcestershire and dash of pepper. Spoon over buttered toast.
Serve 2.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: In medium bowl cream sugar, butter and shortening.
In small bowl, beat eggs until lemon in color.
Mix in large bowl flour, salt and baking powder.
Add eggs, sugar mixture, flavorings and milk.
Blend well.
Bake in greased, floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: quick chili with spaghetti
directions: Fry hamburger and drain grease.
Add stewed tomatoes, and all the ingredients except the spaghetti to the pan.
Add spaghetti and simmer until noodles are done.
Serve.

title: wilted red onions
directions: Put onions in a crockery bowl.
Mix all other ingredients together in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over the onions. When cool, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes good onion sandwiches or a topping for tomatoes or just plain as a side dish. Makes 3 cups.

title: quick stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add mushroom soup, catsup, pepper, salt and paprika.
Heat thoroughly.
Add sour cream.
Remove from heat and mix well.
Serve with noodles.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast and let set for 10 minutes. Add flour, sugar and baking soda; mix with pastry blender until well blended, then add butter Crisco. Blend until looks like coarse crumbs. Add buttermilk. Blend well until ball forms. LET SET OVERNIGHT. DO NOT REFRIGERATE.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Make dough using all ingredients except chicken and gravy. Place chicken and gravy in baking dish.
Drop dough by spoonfuls over chicken and gravy.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned spicy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin with brown sugar, white sugar, molasses, salt and spices.
When mixed well, add eggs; blend well.
Add cream; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: summer's best fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in large baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and nutmeg.
Stir into fruit.
Mix in blender 1 cup flour, milk and butter; spread over fruit.
Combine 1 cup sugar and water in blender.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: angel food cake
directions: Separate egg whites; bring to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour with 3/4 cup sugar three times; set aside. Measure into large mixing bowl the egg whites, salt and cream of tartar.
Beat with wire whip or electric mixer until foamy. Gradually add remaining sugar; continue beating until meringue holds stiff peaks.
Gently fold in extracts.
Sift gradually the flour and sugar mixture over the meringue.
Fold in gently.
Push batter into ungreased tube pan.
Gently cut through batter with knife.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Invert on a funnel.
Keep inverted until cool.

title: jello chiffon cake
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust for a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Dissolve jello in hot water, sugar and juice and rind of lemon. Put in refrigerator until it starts to jell.
Beat Milnot until stiff and whip into jello mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: sauce for smoky hollow sausages
directions: Mix all together and simmer on stove.

title: egg nog
directions: Combine well beaten eggs, condensed milk, vanilla and salt until well blended.
Gradually beat into regular milk.
Gently fold in whipped cream.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.

title: galliano
directions: Boil water and sugar until it makes syrup.
Cool.
Mix vanilla, juice, anise, vodka and food color.
Mix with syrup. Ready to use.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Cut slits and stuff cheese into slits.
Bake at 300 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Add rest of ingredients. Last, fold in cut up cherries and milk.
Double recipe for large loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or more.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine jello, water, and sugar.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Chill over night.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients; cool.
Add yeast that has been dissolved in warm water.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour to make firm soft dough.
Knead well on floured board.
Place in bowl, cover, let rise and punch down.
Roll out to 1-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover; let rise.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yields 18 rolls.

title: cherry delight
directions: In large bowl, mix together the cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple, Eagle Brand milk and whipped topping.
Blend well; pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole and freeze.
This is a beautiful pink and can be frozen in individual molds for parties.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put sugar, butter, syrup and salt in a saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and soda.
Pour syrup over corn in roaster. Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: aunt gail's frankfurters and noodles
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add franks and onions.
Brown.
Add noodles, soup and milk.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil and cover. Turn heat down and simmer.
Thin mixture with milk or water as necessary.
Simmer about 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and cheese.

title: quick arabian stew
directions: Sear and brown pork chops in a skillet.
Remove and place them in a covered casserole dish.
Put 1 tablespoon raw rice on top of each pork chop.
Pour stewed tomatoes over all.
Cover and bake in oven about 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange whip salad
directions: Drain both pineapple and mandarin oranges. Mix all ingredients together. Chill.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onions and celery.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Stir in sauerkraut, noodles, soup and mushrooms; season with salt and pepper.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Spoon into greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter may be kept for several days in covered container in refrigerator.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine gelatin, pecans and coconut.
Stir in milk and vanilla; mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into strawberries.
Roll in red sugar.
Insert slivered almonds in top of berry to form a leaf.
Makes 1 pound and 3 ounces.
Can be frozen.
Enjoy.

title: crescent cookies
directions: *Walnuts can be added if desired.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Wash, drain and hull strawberries; cut in halves or quarters. Add sugar and water; refrigerate 2 hours.
Split biscuits.
Allow 1/2 cup of berries per serving; layer half (1/4 cup) of berries over bottom of biscuit.
Replace top and add remaining berries.

title: jojo's
directions: Mix milk and egg.
Set aside.
Blend dry ingredients.
Cut potatoes into wedges, leaving on the skins.
Dip in egg mixture and roll in dry mixture.
Drop in hot fat and fry 5 minutes or until done.

title: holiday nut roll
directions: Crush wafers in food processor.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into rolls.
Rolls can be rolled in coconut, also.
Chill and slice.
Let stand at room temperature a few minutes prior to serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: venison roast
directions: Cut roast on slant 2 to 3 times on each side and insert a slice of bacon. Peel and cut potatoes and carrots in half. Peel onions and garlic. Line baking pan with heavy foil. Place roast in pan. Arrange potatoes, onions and carrots around roast. Core and seed green peppers and place on vegetables. Slice garlic over mixture. Add water. Cover tightly with heavy foil. Cook 2 1/2 hours in preheated 375° oven. Sprinkle salt and pepper over all ingredients.

title: terry brock's fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix both the cream cheese and marshmallow cream together well.
Chill.
Serve with cut up fruit.

title: garlic breadsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a pie plate, combine melted margarine and garlic salt.
On a lightly floured surface, roll each biscuit into a thin stick about 8-inches long.
Roll sticks in melted garlic butter.
Sprinkle sticks on all sides with sesame seed. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 6 breadsticks.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Grease large pan generously with butter.
Combine ingredients. Pour any box cake mix, mixed according to package directions, and bake as directed.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Saute onion, mushrooms and garlic for 1 minute. Add water.

Cover and cook 3 to 4 minutes. Combine cheese, carrots, spinach, eggs and Parmesan cheese. Layer noodles, 1/2 sauce, 1/2 sauteed vegetables and 1/2 cheese mixture. Repeat and top with Mozzarella. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Simmer, drain and mash squash.
Mix ingredients together and put into greased casserole.
Top with few crumbs.
Bake at 300° just until brown.

title: triple chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In mixer bowl, beat butter, sugars and vanilla until blended.
Add eggs and milk; beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually add to butter mixture blending well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 11 minutes.
Cool 1 minute; remove to wire rack.
Press kisses in center of each cookie.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: chef salad supreme
directions: Toss the lettuce together. Place the cottage cheese in the center of the lettuce. Arrange the shredded meats around the salad. Sprinkle the Roquefort cheese on top. Add the eggs, scallions, carrots, raisins and mushrooms. Top with the Cheddar and Provolone cheese. Serves 10.

title: junes easy biscuits
directions: Mix together. Turn out on floured board. Pat or roll to 3/4-inch thick. Cut out. Turn over in oil. Bake in black iron skillet 8 to 10 minutes in a 450° oven or until done. Makes about 10 biscuits.

title: strawberry rice whip
directions: Cook instant rice as per directions on package.
Blend banana, sugar, sweetener, cool water and cooked rice until smooth and creamy.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add to blended mixture and chill.
When mixture has congealed slightly, whip with electric beater until light and fluffy.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and marshmallow cream together until smooth.
Cut up fruit into bite-sized pieces.
Dip fruit into mixture and enjoy.
Use for an appetizer.

title: ranch stuffed potatoes
directions: Scoop out inside of the potatoes into a bowl and combine with sour cream and Hidden Valley Ranch salad dressing mix.
Fill potato skins with mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375° or microwave until cheese melts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cube when cool.
Save broth.
Mix margarine and crackers together and set aside.
Combine soup, sour cream, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Layer a 2-quart casserole dish that has been buttered with 1/2 of crumb mixture.
Cover with chicken pieces.
Pour over soup mixture and top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled green beans
directions: Use enough water to cover the beans in large pot.
Bring to a full, rolling boil.
Boil one hour.
Pour into clean, hot jars and seal.
You can pour off the liquid when you open a jar.
Add fresh water to finish cooking or leave the canning liquid and finish cooking.
I drain my beans and add fresh water.
Not as tart, but good.

title: mabel's cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix and bake as directed on box.
Pour crushed pineapple in its own juice into a small saucepan and add 3/4 cup sugar.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Pour mixture over cake as soon as removed from oven (after piercing top of cake with a fork). Cool completely.
Combine pudding and milk.
Blend until thick and then spread over cake.
Beat whipping cream until thick and add 10x sugar and beat until stiff.
Spread over cake and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Separate crackers and arrange on bottom of a long cookie sheet.
Melt margarine and real butter; add sugar and cook 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.

title: corn soup with curry
directions: Heat butter in a saucepan and add the onion.
Cook until soft and add minced garlic.
Add the curry powder and flour; stir.
Add the tomato and chicken broth.
Stir well, then let simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour the soup into the container of a food processor; blend, then reheat and add the corn.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat and stir in yogurt.
Sprinkle with chopped basil leaves or parsley.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend all together the ingredients. Spoon into shallow baking dish or quiche dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes until bubbly.
Serve hot with Triscuits.
Serves 25.

title: robby's tasty filled taters
directions: Microwave potatoes until done.
