Cut off 1/2-inch slice from top and scoop out most of potato, leaving shell.
Mash remaining ingredients, adding 1/2 the cheese and refill shells with the mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Microwave for 4 to 5 minutes until cooked through.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Yield:
4 servings.

title: first rate chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar and salt.
Stir in yolks; add milk. Cook in double boiler until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
If using meringue, bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: microwave broccoli bacon quiche
directions: Place bacon on several layers of paper towels.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on High or until slightly undercooked.
Remove and set aside.
Beat eggs with cream and cheese.
Stir in broccoli, salt, garlic powder and lemon pepper.
Crumble bacon. Stir half of the bacon into egg mixture.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Microwave on Medium power for 4 to 6 minutes, stirring every other minute. Continue microwaving on High for 10 minutes or until eggs set.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Top with remaining bacon. Garnish with sliced tomatoes. Serves 4.

title: spaghetti with pesto sauce
directions: Saute oil and garlic until golden, not brown.
Remove from heat and add the rest of the ingredients except the cheese.
Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Drain spaghetti.
Put spaghetti in large bowl.
Pour warm pesto sauce over spaghetti and mix together well.
Sprinkle on cheese as desired.

title: diet banana split cake
directions: Slice cake into 3 layers.
Place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour pineapple over cake.
Layer sliced bananas and then pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with fruit.

title: crab snacks
directions: Mix butter, cheese spread, seasonings and mayonnaise.
Break up crab meat and blend into cheese mixture.
Spread on English muffins.
Cut each half into 6 or 8 triangles.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Yields about 64 bite sized snacks.

title: apple betty pie
directions: Mound apples in buttered 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle with orange juice.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Cut butter or margarine into 12 equal-length sticks.
Chill in freezer while fixing the chicken, for butter should be very cold. Pull skin from chicken breasts.
Halve breasts and cut meat in one piece from bone.
Place each half, with boned side up, between waxed paper and pound very thin with a mallet or a rolling pin to form a "cutlet."
(Be careful not to pound holes in meat.)

title: gumbo file
directions: Remove bones from chicken; cut meat in small pieces (add water to bones and simmer).
Brown chicken in fat with salt and pepper. Remove chicken and put in flour.
Stir until brown and smooth.
Add onion and saute until yellow.
Add tomato.
Put in chicken stock, thyme, cayenne and celery.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add oysters and parsley and cook until edges of oysters curl.
Remove from fire and stir in file.
Serve with large spoonful of hot, fluffy rice in each soup bowl.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Roll into small cocktail size meatballs and brown in oil until cooked.
Drain and set aside.

title: quick soup
directions: Mix in a large pot and cook until done.
Serve with crackers or corn bread.

title: corn bread stove top
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in bowl.
Beat buttermilk and egg and stir into cornmeal mix.
Heat bacon drippings in iron skillet and pour into batter.
Cover and "bake" over low heat for 10 minutes. Invert on cover, slide back into skillet and bake 10 more minutes, until center is done.
Serve in wedges hot.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crushed graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted butter or margarine.
Place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then mix powdered sugar, 2 sticks oleo and whole eggs.
Spread mixture on top of graham cracker crust.
Add bananas on top of this.
Place pineapple on top of bananas.
Top evenly with Cool Whip.
Add chopped pecans to top of Cool Whip.
Top with cherries.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: strawberry pleasure
directions: Place the
wafer
crumbs in an oblong dish and pour the oleo over the crumbs.
Mix well and press into dish as crust.

title: cake-type shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and baking powder.
Stir to blend. Cut in margarine to make crumbs.
Combine molasses, water, baking soda and cinnamon.
Pur 1/3 molasses mixture into pie shell.
Add 1/3 crumb mixture. Continue alternating the 2 mixtures, ending with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Sift salt and soda into flour.
Add nuts; add to first part and mix.
Put dough on well floured board; knead until smooth.
Roll into round roll of desired size; roll in wax paper.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to bake, slice very thin and bake in moderate oven (350°) until crisp.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate bon-bons
directions: Cream together one stick or margarine, powdered sugar and milk.
Add vanilla, coconut and walnuts.
Refrigerate until dough is hardened.
Butter hands and roll into one-inch balls (if dough starts to get soft, place in freezer for period until hard again). Place formed balls into separate bowl.
When all the dough is rolled, refrigerate overnight.

title: custard pie
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Gradually stir in scalded milk. Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 additional minutes.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Heat butter.
Add onion, salt and Accent.
Cook 2 minutes. Stir in flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add salmon liquid.
Cook over moderate heat until mixture thickens.
Stir a little hot sauce into beaten egg, then stir egg into remaining sauce.
Place salmon in casserole.
Then a layer of peas.
Pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften at room temperature for 1 to 2 hours before preparation.
Blend with mixer the cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice until smooth.
Pour mixture in crust. Spoon pie filling over top.
Cover with plastic liner from crust.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: buttercream icing
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and shortening with electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, one cup at a time, beating well on medium speed.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often.
When all sugar is mixed in, icing will appear dry. Add milk and beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Keep icing covered with a damp cloth until ready to decorate.
Keep icing in refrigerator when not in use.

title: irish bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch spring-form pan. In large bowl, combine 2 1/4 cups flour, sugar, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in butter until coarse crumbs form.
Fold in currants.

title: quick chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer 7 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir.
Serve with chow mein noodles.

title: pistachio marble cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of batter into separate bowl and stir in 1/4 cup chocolate syrup.
Spoon alternately into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Zigzag spatula through batter to marbleize. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chicken classic
directions: Boil chicken for 1 hour.
Onion, celery and salt can be added to the water.
Bone chicken.
Lay in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix both soup and the can of milk; pour over chicken.
Melt 1 stick of butter with 1 cup of stock from boiled chicken.
Sprinkle herb stuffing mix on top of chicken.
Pour butter/stock mixture on top of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grapes in red wine
directions: Wash and remove grapes from stems.
Place grapes in saucepan with wine, reserving one tablespoon.
Add to saucepan jam and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat.
Boil gently for approximately 5 minutes or until grapes begin to split open.

title: italian beef supper
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add salt, tomato, water and frozen vegetables.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat, separating the vegetables with a fork and stirring to blend sauce cubes.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Bring again to a boil.
Stir rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: spoon rolls
directions: In a large bowl that can be covered, mix water and yeast until dissolved.
Add beaten egg and shortening; stir well.
Add sugar and flour.
Store in refrigerator, covered, in a large bowl.
Will keep 1 week.

title: spiced honey spareribs
directions: Place ribs in a large covered container.
Blend all ingredients together and pour over ribs.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours, turning often.
Place ribs in a shallow pan on a rack. Bake at 300° for 2 hours turning once.
Baste occasionally.

title: pad thai(stir-fry thai noodles)
directions: Soak noodles in warm water for 30 minutes or until softened. Do not let noodles become mushy.
Drain and discard water.
Set noodles aside.
Heat oil over medium-high heat until hot.
Add garlic and stir-fry for 20 seconds.
Add shrimp and stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Set shrimp aside.
Add eggs, stirring constantly and breaking it into pieces.
Push eggs aside.
Add noodles, vinegar, fish sauce, sugar and paprika and toss gently over medium heat for about 1 to 2 minutes.
Add scallions, bean sprouts and shrimp.
Mix all together for about 2 minutes.
Place noodles on a large platter.
Sprinkle crushed peanuts over noodles and garnish with the coriander sprigs and bean sprouts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In medium saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate and margarine.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes or until mixture is slightly thickened.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pear cake
directions: Add sugar and pecans to pears; let stand 1 hour.
Add eggs, vanilla and oil.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Bake in Bundt pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable paella
directions: Cut zucchini into bite-sized chunks; cut tomatoes into 3/4-inch pieces.
Slice eggplant lengthwise in half, then cut each half crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Dice onion; cut each mushroom in halves or quarters.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, using 1/3 cup hot olive oil, cook onion until tender, add zucchini and mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are golden brown.
Add eggplant and 1 tablespoon olive oil, if needed, and cook, stirring frequently, until eggplant is tender-crisp.
Stir in tomatoes, chicken broth, rice, artichoke hearts, salt, saffron and pepper.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Place skillet in oven or transfer rice mixture to 4-quart casserole and bake, uncovered, until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, about 50 minutes.
Remove skillet from oven, stir in garbanzo beans, olives and frozen peas.
Return to oven to heat through, about 15 minutes.
Serves 8 as a main dish.

title: sweet and easy dessert
directions: Add 1 1/2 tablespoons jam per graham tart mix instant jello pudding and pour over jam until level with top of tart crust. Place in refrigerator and chill until ready for after main meal.

title: gina's roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas and salsa.
Spread mixture onto tortillas.
Roll up tortillas tightly and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate several hours.
Slice with electric knife.
Serve with salsa.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake dessert squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Slice well chilled dough into 30 (1/4-inch) thick slices.
Place 15 slices in bottom of greased pan.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Spoon mixture over cookie dough.
Place remaining dough slices over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is deep golden brown.
Chill completely and cut into squares.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: Soak lettuce in cold water for 1 hour; remove, drain for 2 minutes and wrap in a large towel and put in the refrigerator for 2 hours before using.
Mash anchovy fillets with fork and mix with olive oil.

(If anchovies are omitted, substitute 1 teaspoon of German mustard.) Immediately before making this salad, break lettuce into bite size pieces and place into large salad bowl. Put slightly over 1/2 cup of remaining olive oil/garlic/anchovy mixture on cold lettuce and toss, making certain lettuce is completely covered.
More oil may be used if needed.
Beat egg yolks and spread over top of lettuce.
Squeeze lemon through strainer onto lettuce along with 3 tablespoons of red wine vinegar and a few splashes of Worcestershire.
Toss for one minute. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over salad and toss a few times to mix. Serve immediately with a handful of croutons on each salad.

title: zucchini bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, salt and spices to a boil.
Pour over freshly sliced vegetables and let stand 1 hour.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Pack hot, into hot sterilized jars.
Seal at once with lids and bands that have just been scalded in boiling water.
Store in cool, dry place.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: julie's grandma's baklava
directions: Defrost filo dough (overnight in fridge or 2 hours at room temperature).

title: mississippi mud cake and frosting
directions: Combine eggs and sugar, mixing well.
Add butter and vanilla. Combine cocoa with flour and stir into egg mixture until thoroughly mixed.
Add chopped nuts and coconut, stirring to mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and spread with Marshmallow Creme.
Small marshmallows can be substituted.

title: perky cheese cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender.
Saute green pepper in butter until tender.
Add flour and milk to make cream sauce.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour over cauliflower head.

title: black russian cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix, chocolate pudding, eggs, 1/4 cup Kahlua, 1/4 c. strong coffee, 1/4 c. creme de cacao, and oil together well.
Pour into greased bundt pan and bake at 325 degrees for one hour or until done.
Test with toothpick or clean knife.
Mix powdered sugar, 1 Tbsp. creme de cacao, 1 Tbsp. Kahlua, and 1 Tbsp. strong coffee well.
Spoon over warm cake.

title: mamma kelly's brunswick stew
directions: Cook hog head and hens; grind meat.
(Boston butt, souse meat or other pork may be used.)
Cook hamburger, stirring to make it crumble apart.
Drain.
Peel, dice, salt and cook potatoes and onions.
Drain all vegetables (except soup and tomatoes) including potatoes and onions.
Combine all ingredients with salt and pepper to taste in big heavy pot.
Bring to a boil on medium heat, stirring continuously, as it burns easily.
Turn heat down; stir and simmer and simmer and stir until stew is thick and all flavors are mixed.
Feeds multitudes.
Cut recipe in half if you don't plan to feed a big crowd.
Freezes well.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil, vinegar, lime juice, onion, garlic, pepper sauce, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and marinate at least 1 hour at room temperature or overnight in fridge.
Light broiler.
Remove chicken from marinade; save marinade.
Broil chicken and baste frequently with reserved marinade.
Cook until chicken is opaque.
Warm tortillas in pan with low heat.
Keep turning tortillas until soft.
Bring to warm plate.
Coat tortillas with sour cream and salsa.
Add chicken, lettuce and cheese.
Roll and tuck ends.
Try your own variations with peppers or tomatoes added.

title: fat-free salsa dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salsa with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Serve with vegetables or low-fat chips.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Cook ground meat and onions together in skillet with a lid. When meat is cooked, add eggplant, bell pepper, and cooked rice (or cornbread). Salt and pepper to taste. Cook on low heat until eggplants and bell pepper are cooked. This will serve a family of five.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Prepare and boil potatoes; cool.
Add celery, onion and sweet relish.
Combine salad dressing, sugar, celery seed, vinegar and mustard.
Add eggs.

title: cherry squares
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spread in jelly roll pan after mixing.
Cut into squares (16 to 20) and drop cherry pie filling in the middle of each square.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. While still warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy punch
directions: Chill white grape juice and ginger ale. Mix together and serve. You can serve with any fresh fruit sliced on top or frozen into a mold.

title: poor man's cake(eggless-butterless-milkless)
directions: Boil sugar, water, cinnamon, cloves, shortening, nutmeg, salt and raisins together for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Then add flour and baking soda.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased cake pan or dripping pan (14 x 10 x 2-inches).
Bake in 375° oven about 1 hour, or until firm.

title: poor boy bread pudding
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs. Add sugar, margarine, vanilla and milk or buttermilk.
Stir in nutmeg and cinnamon. Add raisins, nuts and coconut, if desired. Break up biscuits and blend in.
Pour into oven-safe casserole dish. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until mixture is set.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brush mushroom caps with butter; set aside. Combine remaining ingredients. Fill caps. Place on broiler pan, filled side up. Broil 6-inches from heat about 5 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and golden and mushrooms are heated through.

title: grits pie
directions: Mix thoroughly by hand.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with flaky coconut, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: warm apple pudding
directions: Peel and slice apples in 8 x 8-inch baking dish, buttered well. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apple slices.
Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Add shortening and milk, beat 2 minutes.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry scones
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Combine egg and milk; add to flour mixture and stir lightly.
Add blueberries.
Spread in a greased 9-inch round layer pan, using back of spoon to smooth it.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mrs. smith's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in top of a double boiler.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth. Cool.

title: bartley's irish creme
directions: Put in blender and mix well, then blend again, at least 3 or 4 times.
Keep in refrigerator!!

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Mix together and press in pan. Bake until golden brown at 350° for 12 minutes. Watch carefully not to burn.

title: fig-strawberry jam
directions: Put figs, sugar and jello in pot.
Bring to a boil.
Stir until it boils.
Then simmer 20 minutes or more.
Stir once in a while, as it boils.
Pour into jars and seal with wax.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix and pour into baked crust.
Bake 35 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: french onion dip
directions: Mix sour cream, soup mix and a dash of Worcestershire sauce together and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: crackling bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg.
Mix well.
Add cracklings and pour into hot greased baking pan or iron skillet and bake at 425° until brown.

title: pineapple swirl coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour an oblong pan (13 x 9-inch) or two (8 x 8-inch) square pans.
Mix 2/3 cup cake mix, brown sugar, nuts and margarine until crumbly.
Reserve.
Beat eggs; blend in sour cream.
Mix into remaining cake mix.
Spread half of batter into pan, top with half of pineapple and sprinkle with half nut mixture.
Do next layer the same.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: uncle bob's fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and beat in peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Pour into 9 x 9 square pan. Cool thoroughly at room temperature before cutting into squares.

title: muskatrollar
directions: Brown ground beef in oleo.
Add onions, chili powder, salt, pepper, mushrooms and tomato juice.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Put in casserole and pour meat
mixture over it.
Add Worcestershire. Sprinkle over top.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Just before serving, sprinkle cheese on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brownie delight
directions: Prepare brownies according to box.
Prepare chocolate mousse according to box directions and refrigerate 1 hour.
Take a knife and cut up brownies real fine, then layer some brownies on the bottom of a nice glass bowl.
On top of the brownies, put 3 or 4 tablespoons of chocolate mousse and spread over brownies.
On top of chocolate mousse, put 3 or 4 tablespoons of Cool Whip and spread over chocolate mousse.
Continue layering brownies, mousse and Cool Whip at least 3 times.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: lemon-coconut freeze
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Beat egg yolks in large bowl until thick.
Stir in milk, lemon juice and rind until well blended.
Fold in 1 2/3 cups of the coconut and whipped topping. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into lemon mixture.
Spoon over crumb crust.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut. Freeze until firm, about 5 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: caramel icing
directions: Place light brown sugar and 6 tablespoons milk in pan.
Melt over medium heat.
Add melted margarine and salt.
Bring to a boil for about 2 minutes or until mixed.
Add 1/4 cup milk and stir. Remove from heat and cool for one minute.
Fold in powdered sugar and spread on cake.

title: sausage gravy
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook sausage and onion until the sausage is no longer pink. Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet. Stir flour into sausage and drippings until blended. Cook and stir until golden brown. Gradually stir in milk and seasonings. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thick. Serve over biscuits. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: curry peaches
directions: Melt butter in a flat baking dish (10-inch square Corning Ware skillet).
Add brown sugar and curry powder.
Stir to make a sauce.
Add raisins.
Place peach halves in pan; spoon sauce over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Spoon sauce over peaches once during baking.
Serve hot.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Add rhubarb, sugar, tapioca or cornstarch, crushed pineapple and strawberry jello dissolved in hot water.
Pour over dish and lace crust on top.
Bake at about 400° until crust is brown.

title: mama's molasses cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour, and mix well. Gradually add flour until you have a stiff dough.
Roll out and cut into desired shapes.
(Great for gingerbread men.) Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Cook rice.
To hot cooked rice, add small jar of Cheez Whiz.
Stir until cheese dissolves.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and box of thawed broccoli.
Stir.
Cook in oven for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Mix together butter, brown sugar, oatmeal, vanilla and salt. Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Microwave chocolate chips and peanut butter until melted.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over cooled oatmeal mixture.
Allow to completely cool before cutting.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Lightly grease pan or baking dish.
Using meat mallet or edge of saucer, pound chicken until 1/4-inch thick.
Combine cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Combine egg and 1 tablespoon of wine.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and then in cracker crumb mixture to coat.
Arrange chicken in prepared dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini goulash
directions: Brown ground chuck.
While meat is cooking, add onion.
When in season, add zucchini.
Add tomatoes and macaroni, cooked.
(If you like, you can also add 1 cup cubed Velveeta cheese.)
Cook about 20 minutes to blend flavors.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and margarine together with mixer. Mix 2 packages vanilla pudding and 4 cups cold milk with wire whisk.
Mix pudding and cream cheese.
Mix together and blend in Cool Whip.
Layer in glass bowl the Oreo cookie crumbs, cream cheese, pudding mix, cookie crumbs, cream cheese and pudding mix, ending with Oreo cookie crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.
May put in flower pots and add gummy worms for decoration.

title: quick muffins
directions: Mix, put in greased muffin tins about 1/2 full.
(They rise high.)
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 large muffins.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Pour 1 cup hot water over jello.
Add strawberries, banana and pineapple.
Pour half jello mixture in dish; chill.
Pour sour cream over this mixture, then pour remaining jello mixture over cream (three layers).
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: deshea's cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add rest of recipe.
Stir; pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: awesome cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar, eggs, brown sugar and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients, except coconut and Rice Krispies. Mix well.
Then carefully add coconut and Rice Krispies.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pork nasube
directions: Fry
nasube
in oil.
When done, place on paper towels. Cook pork
in oil with crushed garlic.
Add mushrooms, sugar, chili pepper, water and shoyu.
Simmer for a few minutes, then add the nasube and round onion.

title: puffy baked pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly beat flour, milk, vanilla and eggs together; batter should be lumpy.
Melt butter in a 10 to 12-inch skillet until pan and butter are hot.
Pour in batter. Bake 15 to 20 minutes until puffy and golden.
Sprinkle top of pancake with confectioners sugar.

title: quick chicken pasta soup
directions: Cook chicken, onion and garlic in olive oil in large pan on medium heat. Stir frequently until chicken is cooked and onion tender (about 5 minutes). Add remaining ingredients, except pasta. Bring to a boil. Stir in pasta. Reduce heat and cover. Simmer until pasta is tender, about 12 minutes. Makes 8 cups.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute the onion in butter in a saucepan.
Add seasonings and bread cubes; stir until well mixed.
Arrange 1 can of the stewed tomatoes in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with half the bread mixture.
Repeat the layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry pie in casserole
directions: Grease 1 1/2-inch casserole dish.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add dry ingredients.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Add milk and mix into a stiff dough.
Spread dough into bottom of casserole.
Pour cherries over the dough.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar and pour juice over top evenly.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: tommy's mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, sugar, Wesson oil and eggs.
Add mandarin oranges (with juice).
Mix well for 2 minutes or longer. Use two 8-inch or 9-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Put the crackers in a plastic bag and roll with a rolling pin to make the crumbs.
Set aside.
Mince the onion.
Set aside. Break egg in mixing bowl and beat. Add corn, onion, milk, salt and pepper to egg in mixing bowl.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Dot with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello. Add the rest of the ingredients and let set until firm.

title: mary greco's italian meatballs
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl and then roll into medium-size balls.
Cook in about a 1/2-inch of oil until medium to dark brown (10 to 15 minutes).
Drain and place in spaghetti sauce or eat with brown gravy.

title: stir-fry rice and beef
directions: Cut meat into thin slices, about 1-inch long.
Cut onion in wedges and pepper in thin strips, removing seeds.

title: barbecue sauce for grilled chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.

title: angel food ice cream cake
directions: Cut the cake in half; tear one half into small pieces and set aside.
Cut the other half into 12 to 14 thin slices; arrange in the bottom of a waxed paper-lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, overlapping as needed.
Spread softened ice cream over cake, pressing down to smooth.
Gently press the small cake pieces into ice cream.
Cover and freeze.
Just before serving, slice strawberries and sweeten to taste.
Cut dessert into squares and top with strawberries.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: festive shrimp and fettucini
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook shrimp, green pepper, garlic and crushed red pepper until shrimp turn pink. Stir in soup, water and vinegar.
Heat through.
Serve over fettucini.
Makes 4 servings.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: wilma's stuffed bell peppers
directions: Saute onion.
Brown beef in skillet.
Cut bell peppers and remove seeds.
Stuff pepper with rice, salt, pepper, ground beef and onion; top with sauce.
Place in a dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until peppers are tender.

title: special sweet potato bake
directions: In large greased casserole dish, layer apple filling, yams then cherry filling.
Over this add juice from yams.
Sprinkle cinnamon and allspice over top.
Add butter dotted over this. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: mom's fruitcake
directions: Beat together the butter, sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
Then set aside.
Next, sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Gradually beat the dry ingredients into the egg batter.
Add the flavorings after the dry ingredients.
Stir in the fruits and nuts last.
Pour into greased and floured pans. The mixture will be extremely thick.
Bake in a slow oven at 200° overnight.
Great smell to wake up to!
Makes 16 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer as listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add coconut and chopped pecans.
Cook until golden brown, stirring.
Set aside.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini into lengthwise pieces about 2 to 3 inches long and quartered.
Boil in salty water until tender.
Drain.
Cut up tomatoes and onion.
Mix all 3 ingredients.
Top with heavy layer of bacon bits.
Scatter bits of margarine on top of bacon bits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together sugars and shortening until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup candies.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Press 2 or 3 additional into each cookie.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars, oleo and salad oil.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar together.
Add to mixture.
Mix well. Roll into balls about the size of a walnut.
Roll in granulated sugar and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes at least 6 dozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken; remove and cool.
Reserve 1 1/2 to 2 cups broth. Mix soups, onion and garlic with broth; simmer.
Take cooled chicken and cut into small pieces.
Add sour cream to sauce after it has simmered a few minutes.
Make sure sauce is blended together well.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pour 1/2 cup of sauce, spreading to cover bottom of dish.
Take 1/2 of chicken, 1/2 slice of pepper and 1 slice cheese, rolling it up into tortilla.
Make remaining enchiladas, placing in dish as you go along.
Cover with remaining sauce, cheese and pepper.
Heat in oven at 350° until bubbly.

title: e z punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on ice.
tags: packs unsweet strawberry drink mix powder

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: german meat balls
directions: Combine meat and add other ingredients.
Make 1-inch balls and roll in flour.
In skillet, heat 1 can of beef bouillon and 1 cup of water.
Add meat balls and bring to a boil.
Lower heat. Simmer 30 minutes.
Thicken with 1 tablespoon flour and 1/4 cup water.
Add lemon slices.

title: vegetable cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup chopped pecans. Shape into ball. Chill, then roll in remaining pecans. Store in refrigerator. May also be frozen for future use.

title: hollywood chicken
directions: Brown pork in a skillet; drain.
Mix soup (undiluted) with meat and about 1 handful of chips.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with another handful of chips the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash and dry lettuce and tear into large salad bowl.
Cook bacon until crisp, crumble and reserve.
To bacon fat in skillet, stir in 1/4 cup sliced green onions, sugar, salt, pepper, and vinegar.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Pour hot dressing over lettuce. Sprinkle with bacon bits and chopped egg and toss to coat evenly. Serves 2 or 3.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an angel food cake pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each one. Add flavorings, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Cook for 60 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage, celery, green pepper and carrots very fine. Mix together sugar, oil, vinegar and salt; stir until dissolved. Pour this mixture over salad.

title: applebutter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly, then blend in dry ingredients and finally add the applebutter.
You may also use applesauce; that is what the original recipe called for, but I was out one day and thought I would try applebutter and it worked out fine.
Bake cookies at 350°.

title: pot roast(sunday dinner)
directions: Place all ingredients in roasting pan or crock-pot.
Cover roast with water.
Season with garlic and seasoned salt.
Bake or cook at 275° about 4 hours.

title: hostess twinkie cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch glass dish, pour the pineapple and juice. Lay Twinkies over pineapple and smash lightly. Mix pudding as directed on box and pour over the Twinkies. Spread sliced bananas over pudding and layer Cool Whip over the bananas. Keep cool.

title: tabbouleh(syrian salad)
directions: Cover the cracked wheat with cold water and let stand 1 hour. Drain well and squeeze all water out. Chop and clean vegetables and add to cracked wheat. Add lemon juice, olive oil and seasonings to taste. Mix well and chill for several hours. Taste again to be sure it has a very minty and lemony flavor. Pile on a bowl or platter and garnish with tomatoes. Can be used as an appetizer or a summer vegetable dish. Additions of cubed cucumbers, raw zucchini or yellow squash are good, but not authentic. Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir to blend.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve in hollowed out round French bread or Hawaiian bread. Use hollowed out bread for dipping.

title: pesto sauce
directions: In electric blender container, combine all ingredients.
Blend or process for 30 seconds or until mixture is smooth.
Store in covered container and refrigerate.

title: tater pie
directions: Combine nutmeg, cinnamon, and sugar.
Mix in baking powder. Stir butter into hot mashed potatoes.
Add baking soda and milk. Beat eggs until frothy.
Combine everything and blend until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Reduce heat and bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: cranberry jelly
directions: Boil the cranberry juice, lemon juice and pectin, stirring constantly.
Do not remove from heat.
Add the sugar; continue stirring constantly, bringing to hard boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and jar as for any jelly.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box. Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients together in larger bowl and mix well. Serve.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Warm taco shells in oblong pan.
Brown hamburger meat and drain, then add taco mix.
Cut up lettuce, tomato and onion.
Put over soft taco shells.
Add hamburger mixture over lettuce, tomato and onion.
Put shredded cheese in saucepan on low heat.
Add milk, stirring slowly, until cheese has melted.
Pour cheese sauce over hamburger and serve.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Cut up and frizzle dried beef in 1/2 stick of oleo. Cook noodles and drain. Grate 1/2 of the cheese and mix all of the ingredients together.
Put in baking dish. Top with the remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes quite a large serving.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Mix beans and seasoning mix.
Spread on bottom of 9-in. pie plate.
Layer remaining ingredients over bean mixture. Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 6-8.

title: salted nut logs
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme, sugar and vanilla in mixer until it sticks together.
Take
a
part
of
it and roll into a log about 5/8-inch
in
diameter.
Cut
into	about
1-inch
logs. Freeze. Melt
caramels,
margarine	and condensed milk.
Roll frozen logs in caramel mixture, then nuts.
Freeze well.
Logs coat more easily when frozen.
The other half can of condensed milk can be put
in
a plastic container in the freezer to be used later.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine these ingredients. Put 2 tablespoons oil or grease in iron skillet. Pour batter in the heated skillet. Bake at 450° until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In large pressure cooker, combine chicken, onions, potatoes, carrots and mixed vegetables and cook on high until top starts to rock and turn back to medium and cook 15 minutes.
Let steam off and drain all except 1 1/2 cups of liquid. Remove chicken, skin and bones.
Add soups and mix in large 3-quart casserole dish. Mix Bisquick and milk and pat to shape on top of casserole dish, about 1/2-inch thick.
Layer on top of mixture and bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken-rice bake
directions: Arrange rice in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine soups in large saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Heat over medium heat.
Pour over rice layer.
Arrange chicken over rice. Sprinkle with dry soup mix.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake in a 325° oven for 2 hours or until chicken is tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: waffle pancake topping
directions: Can use banana with a squeeze of lemon.
Can use fresh raspberries or strawberries.
Can use fresh pineapple or blueberries thickened with some cornstarch.
Can use fresh peaches, apricots, cherries sweetened with apple juice and thickened with cornstarch for a delicious topping.

title: oriental salad dressing
directions: Mix together in bottle and shake well. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange half of sliced potatoes in 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with half the flour, salt and onions.
Repeat. Pour in milk and dot with butter.
Microwave (High) covered, 15 to 18 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn every 4 minutes.
Rest covered 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Garnish with paprika or parsley.

title: anne's easy artichoke quiche
directions: Place all ingredients into a bowl and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Test for doneness by inserting a knife into the center of the quiche.
If still raw, allow another 5 or 10 minutes.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat or put in jar and shake.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzel crumbs, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pack in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°, stirring twice.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Drain the sauerkraut and set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large saucepan, saut mushrooms, peppers and onions in a little butter until soft. Add sauerkraut, tomatoes and sliced sausage mixing well after each addition.
Place in a covered dish and bake for 1 hour.
If casserole is too juicy, uncover and bake for additional 30 minutes.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into a prepared pie crust. Cover with top crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Feeds 4 to 6 persons.

title: low-fat taco soup
directions: Brown the ground round beef. Drain and rinse beef with hot water to remove grease. Add browned beef to all remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: triple chocolate treat
directions: Cook and cool brownies; tear apart.
In a large mixing bowl, prepare instant chocolate pudding per package directions.
Cool until set.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread avocados over bean dip.
Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning; spread over avocados.
Top with chopped tomatoes, chopped black olives, chopped green onions, and grated Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix the first 8 items in order with electric blender on medium speed.
Spoon fold in apples and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until crisp and tender. Drain.
Set aside to cool.
In a 2-quart container, cut onion and pepper into thin round slices. Add cooled carrots. Set aside.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine soup, oil, mustard, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well and pour over vegetables. Stir lightly to make sure all vegetables are coated.
Marinate in refrigerator for 12 hours or more.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes (enough for 9 x 13-inch baking dish).
Grease baking dish.
Sprinkle flour in dish.
Layer sliced potatoes with cheese cut in strips.
Put another layer of potatoes, then a layer of margarine on cheese and potatoes.
Sprinkle another layer of flour; put about 3 or 4 layers of potatoes and cheese, margarine, flour, etc. (onions optional).
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour can of cream with equal part water over dish.
Cover. Bake at 375° until done.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: mom's peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Place 9 peach halves cut side down into butter and brown sugar.
In a separate bowl, beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Add sugar and continue beating until smooth.
Beat in peach juice and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and fold into egg yolk mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour batter over the peaches in baking pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
While cake is still warm, turn onto cake plate.

title: crock-pot swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving pieces. Season with salt and pepper.
Coat with flour and brown in small amount of oil.
Place in crock-pot with sliced onion.
Pour tomatoes over all. Cover and set to high temperature for 1 hour, then to low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: gala pecan spread
directions: Blend cheese and milk.
Add beef (shredded), pepper and spices.
Add sour cream.
Put in square dish.
Heat pecans in butter.
Sprinkle on top of sour cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve on crackers or rye bread.

title: mock oyster fondue
directions: Boil broccoli as directed on package. Drain well. Saut onions and celery in oleo until tender. Add garlic cheese and mushroom soup. Cook until cheese melts, stirring often. Add 2 tablespoons flour. Add mushroom pieces and broccoli. Serve warm with your favorite crackers.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for tomato juice.
Form meat balls.
Pour tomato juice over meat balls in electric skillet. Start cooking at 375° but reduce heat to simmer when food starts to boil.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together Kool-Aid, water and pineapple juice.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
To serve, place punch base in a punch bowl and spoon in small scoops of ice cream.
Pour 7-Up slowly over ice cream and base.
It should foam slightly.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and yogurt.
Mix with all other ingredients. Cover and chill for 2 hours.

title: cat skinner cake
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in mixing bowl. Mix at medium speed for 5 minutes. Fold in the drained pineapple and pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done in a 9 x 13 pan.

title: no fuss oven baked carrots
directions: Place in dish.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and pour over top of cream cheese layer.
Congeal.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: almond roca cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except for chocolate and nuts.
Spread thinly on oiled cookie sheet.
(The batter will be stiff and hard to spread to the ends of the cookie sheet, but it can be done and there is enough batter.)
Bake at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes.
Melt chocolate in a double boiler and spread on cookies while they are still warm.
Sprinkle immediately with nuts and cut.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until done.
Rinse with cold water.
Mix with veggies and dressing.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of Salad Supreme.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients 24 hours before using.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Place chicken, water, 2 teaspoons salt, onion salt and celery salt in Dutch oven.
Simmer, covered, until tender (1 to 1 1/4 hours).
Add water as needed.
Remove chicken to bowl.
Cool, then remove meat from bones in medium-size pieces.
Remove 2 1/2 cups broth from pan; reserve.
To rest of broth, add 3 quarts of water and 2 tablespoons salt.
Bring to boil.
Slowly add spaghettini. Cook 6 minutes or until tender-crisp, stirring occasionally. Drain well and place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: veal alla bistrot
directions: Place egg whites and yolks into bowl and beat until smooth. Dip veal strips into batter until covered.
Wrap Swiss cheese first, then Prosciutto around veal, then dip again into egg batter.
Cover both sides with bread crumbs and place into preheated frying pan with olive oil.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese to taste and fry to a golden brown.
Serve with Italian bread, garden salad and beverage of your choice.

title: freezer biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt. Cut in the shortening.
Beat egg and milk together; add to flour mixture.
Knead, roll out dough and cut biscuits.
Bake immediately or freeze.
Do not thaw before baking.
Bake in 425°. Bake fresh biscuits for about 10 minutes, frozen biscuits for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: mexican chicken stew
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook 5 minutes, stirring often. Remove chicken from skillet and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients, except onions; mix well.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat to medium and cook 10 minutes. Stir in cooked chicken and onion. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla, mix well. Gradually add flour, cocoa, baking soda, and salt. Then stir in chocolate chips. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cookies will be gooey. Do not overcook.

title: crazy crust cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Melt margarine in 9x13 inch pan.
In bowl combine flour, sugar and milk.
Spoon batter over melted margarine.
Spoon the pie filling over batter.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Pour dry croutons in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble sausage over top.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Mix soup, milk, mustard and 6 beaten eggs.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning place in preheated 350 degree oven for 1 hour or until set.

title: strawberry fondue dip for fresh fruit
directions: In a blender,
blend
ingredients together until smooth and the consistency of	whipped
cream.
Use the drained juice only if needed.
Serve for	a
dip	with
fresh fruit.
If not sweet to suit your taste, add a little more sugar.

title: quick hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add mushrooms and soup; simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream; salt to taste.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: mandarin chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings at the joint with a sharp knife.
Discard wing tips.
Scrape and push meat to one end of the bone, so that each piece resembles a small drumstick.
Refrigerate, covered, until ready to use.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with non-stick coating.
Mix vegetables, onion, cheese, and mayonnaise and pour into casserole dish.
Cover with crushed crackers and drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown but bubbly.

title: make ahead cheese ball
directions: Chop dried beef into fine pieces; reserve a small amount. Chop onion fine.
Let cream cheese get soft.
Add onion and dried beef.
Form into a ball and pat reserved dried beef onto the outside of ball.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: lo-cal cherry cobbler
directions: Place cherries in an 8-inch pie plate or shallow baking pan. Measure remaining cherry juice.
Add water, if necessary, to measure 2/3 cup.
In a saucepan, combine cherry juice, cornstarch, lemon juice, 1/4 teaspoon liquid sweetener and almond extract.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over cherries.

title: beef taco dip
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Add beans, tomato sauce, onion, mustard and taco seasoning.
Bring to a boil and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix sour cream and chili powder; pour over top.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and add shredded cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour Bundt pan. Mix all ingredients in 2-quart bowl and beat on low speed for 30 seconds and for 4 minutes on medium, scraping the sides and bottom often. Pour batter into Bundt pan and bake for 50 minutes, then check for doneness. Bake a little longer if pick inserted in middle comes out sticky.

title: best beets
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Add vinegar and water; bring to a boil. All all remaining ingredients. Reduce heat. Simmer until heated through.

title: turkey rub
directions: Rinse and pat turkey dry. Mix salt and oil together. Rub the outside and cavity of turkey. Use the remainder of the salt and oil mixture with the pepper and parsley; mixing well; rub this mixture in cavity and outside. Bake at 325° for the amount of time specified per pound of turkey.

title: cool cream sicle
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour over ice and garnish with fruit. Yum, yum.
Makes a lot of drinks.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring to a boil: brown sugar, margarine and white syrup and boil for 5 minutes.
Then add the baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix well and pour over the popped corn.

title: creamed beef
directions: Cut dried beef into pieces.
Melt 1/4 cup of margarine in a saucepan; stir in 1/4 cup of flour and pepper.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add dry beef.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve hot over toast, biscuits, potatoes or rice.

title: blueberry stacked cake
directions: Mix well; place batter in 6 small pans, or in 3 and evenly cut into halves after baking to come up with six layers.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: mark and richard's quick salsa chicken
directions: Microwave:
Sprinkle both sides of chicken with seasoning mix. Place chicken in a baking dish.
Pour salsa over chicken.
Cover with wax paper and microwave for approximately 9 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and microwave 60 seconds or until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream.
Serves 2.

title: cracked pepper steak
directions: Slash fat edges of stake.
Sprinkle all surfaces of steak with tenderizer, using about 1/2 tsp. per pound of meat.
(DO NOT SALT.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine diced chicken, soups and milk.
In another bowl, mix melted butter and stuffing mix and pour on top of casserole mix. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Turn off.
Blend in flour with wire whisk; set aside.
In Dutch oven, combine bouillon cubes and water.
Heat over high heat until cubes dissolve.
Add half and half, broccoli, soda and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in flour mixture.
Reduce heat.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes, stirring often.
Yields 16 servings.

title: raspberry plant food
directions: Put a handful to each berry stalk once a month in February, March and April, and again when they have small berries and in the fall.

title: lemon rub pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar, flour and corn meal. Add eggs, melted butter, milk, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until top is a pretty brown.
Cut while warm.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Thaw orange juice.
Whip orange juice, margarine and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla wafers.
Let mixture chill 30 minutes.
Mix again.
Chill again.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in coconut.
Store in covered container.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast cakes in warm tap water.
Stir and keep warm. Mix oil, eggs and buttermilk; add to yeast.
Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Add flour mixture to liquid until firm.
(Do not beat too much.)
Knead on a floured board or pastry cloth.
Shape in a ball in a greased bowl.
Cover.
Let rise double.
Punch down.
Let rise double a second time.
Roll out; cut in biscuit shape (fold over for Parker House style).
Let rise.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Mash with potato masher. Add margarine; beat egg, onion, bell pepper and mayonnaise.
Stir well.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Brown bread real crisp. Crumble up bread and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until done (about 1 hour).

title: apple cupcakes
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Alternate milk and dry ingredients.
Lastly, add apples, raisins and nuts.
Mix only until blended.
Pour into muffin tins (15 or 18).
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen.

title: holupki - stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown onion in hot fat.
Add beef, pork, rice and seasonings. Mix well.
Cook separated cabbage leaves in boiling water for several minutes until soft enough to roll.
When cool, place 1 heaping tablespoon of meat mixture on each leaf and roll up and tuck in sides.
Take 1/2 of the sauerkraut and place in bottom of saucepan, then cabbage rolls in layers, then the other half of the sauerkraut.
Pour 1 can of tomato soup and enough water to cover. Cook slowly in covered saucepan about 1 hour.

title: frozen banana split yogurt cake
directions: Remove chocolate frozen yogurt from freezer.

title: orange or lemon dessert
directions: Crush crackers; combine with 1 cup powdered sugar and 1 melted stick oleo or butter.
Put crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch dish and save some crumbs for top.
Mix Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and frozen juice; spread on crumbs.
Sprinkle some crumbs on top.

title: hot dogs and beans
directions: Cook hot dogs until cooked.
Heat beans until hot.
Only cook 239 beans!
One more is 240.

title: pineapple side dish
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick vegetable spray.
Put undrained pineapple in pan.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar and flour; sprinkle over pineapple.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix crackers and butter in separate bowl and cover pineapple with butter/cracker mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Add buttermilk and extract; mix well.
Pour into well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick test comes out clean.

title: bacon poles
directions: On a plate, place two layers of paper towels.
Wrap strips of bacon around each bread stick in a spiral fashion.
Place on paper towel, not touching each other.
Do eight at a time.
Arrange in a circle.
Cover with single layer paper towel and microwave 4 to 5 minutes on High or until bacon is crisp.
Repeat.

title: 49'er cookies
directions: Mix together and spread into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in baking pan before cutting.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread Bisquick mix, pizza
dough
or crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake at 325° until brown.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise
and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing
mix. Spread this
mixture
over	baked
crust.
Sprinkle vegetables over mixture and crust.
Top with cheese.

title: original "shrimp jennifer"
directions: Dice onion and finely chop garlic.
Heat in small amount of oil until transparent. Add ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar, liquid smoke, water, salt and pepper to taste and simmer 10 minutes. Peel and devein shrimp.
Wrap with 1 strip of bacon and place in small casserole dish.
Cover with barbecue sauce. Bake at 450° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: pastor's easy chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions in large pan.
Drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce and the same amount of water as tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Easy!

title: hot lettuce dressing
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry crisp.
Beat eggs.
Add vinegar, sugar and water.
Mix well and pour into bacon pieces. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil a minute or two.
Do not let curdle.
Remove from heat, pour over lettuce, dandelion or steamed shredded cabbage.
Add a little salt and stir.

title: nippy peanut olives
directions: Drain
and
dry
olives with paper towels.
Mix cheese, garlic and
lemon	juice
until soft and fluffy.
Shape cheese over olives with wet fingers to cover completely.
Roll coated olives in chopped peanuts and chill.
Makes 18.

title: to make sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine in blender, milk, sugar, water, oleo and corn syrup. Blend until smooth and thick.
Put in jar in refrigerator.

title: cabbage rolls with beef
directions: Place cabbage head into pot of boiling water.
Turn off heat and let
cabbage
stand
in hot water about 10 minutes to soften. Mix the
cooked
rice,
one chopped onion, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper,
ground
beef
and egg.
Drain
cabbage
leaves. Spoon mound of rice mixture into center of leaf, tuck in sides and fold ends
over	securely.
Place stuffed cabbage leaves, seam side down
in glass dish.
Add tomatoes, onions, bouillon and 1 teaspoon
salt.
Place
in	325° oven for one hour, covered. Remove cover, add lemon juice and brown sugar; continue cooking, uncovered, 30 minutes longer.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch. Add water gradually, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add butter, lemon juice and nutmeg.

title: holy fudgeness
directions: In microwave or over stove, melt chips and butter, add other ingredients (except vanilla).
Bring to a boil.
Cook about 6 minutes.
If cooked over stove, stir constantly.
Add vanilla.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
While broccoli is cooking, mix together mayonnaise, chopped onion, grated cheese and soup.
Put broccoli in a casserole dish.
Pour mixture over top. Sprinkle with stuffing and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Mix cream cheese, mustard and honey; coat chicken breasts.
Put in ungreased pan and top with salad dressing.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Serve topped with cheese or over rice and topped with cheese.

title: turkey lorraine
directions: Cook and drain	broccoli and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish.
In
a large bowl, mix together the meat, soup, mushrooms, lemon
juice and mayonnaise.
Make the dressing per the directions	on
package and spread over the mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Dip chicken in buttermilk, then in seasoned flour. Brown for 5 minutes, turning frequently. Cover and reduce heat to 325°.
Cook for 15 minutes, turning occasionally. Remove cover and fry another 5 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Stir constantly until it comes to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute or until thick.

title: sweet and sour cabbage soup
directions: Brown meat in heavy pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover. Simmer 2 hours.
Cabbage does not get mushy due to lemon juice and tomatoes. Good served with cornbread.
Serves 8.

title: bread and butter pickle slices
directions: Combine cucumber, onion, sweet pepper and whole garlic cloves. Add salt.
Cover with cracked ice; mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours; drain well.
Remove garlic.

title: candied dill pickles
directions: Drain juice off
pickles
and
pour sugar over pickles. Pour vinegar over this.
When sugar melts let sit overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix peas, celery and onions together in casserole dish.
Melt butter; add to stuffing mix.
Pour over pea mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy grilled chicken
directions: Mix dressing and soy sauce. Marinate chicken 3 hours or overnight. Cook on grill or bake.

title: magic salad
directions: Prepare jello with 1 cup hot water, then 1 cup cold water. Let set slightly, then add cheese, celery and drained pineapple. Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: quick chocolate cookies(weight watchers)
directions: For each cookie:
Spread 1 tablespoon Marshmallow Creme between 2 crackers.
Kroger crackers come in 2 x 2-inch squares.

title: corn and black bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Drain corn.
Mix together with pepper and onion in a refrigerator bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients with wire whisk; pour over veggies and stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: melba's delight
directions: Combine ingredients and press in 9 x 14 Pyrex pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: applesauce christmas decoration
directions: Cool.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Put hole in top with nail for string.
Dry for 6 to 7 days in dry warm place.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and chocolate together.
Add sugar. Mix well.
Blend in vanilla, salt and nuts.
Spread into well-greased pan.
Chill 15 minutes or until firm.

title: peanut butter chocolate pudding
directions: Make instant pudding according to box.
Add peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Whip all together and refrigerate in serving dishes. Makes 8 servings.

title: bourdeaulaise sauce
directions: Saute the garlic, celery, onion and tomatoes.
Add the beef stock, mushrooms and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken in water until tender.
Cool, bone, skin and chop chicken.
Place chicken, onions and Veg-All in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Season to taste.
Combine broth and soup; pour over chicken and vegetables.
Combine flour, milk and butter.
Spoon over top of mixture.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour until brown and bubbly. Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: uncle bruce's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine Crisco and sugars, cream thoroughly.
Add vanilla, eggs and cream mixture again thoroughly.
Add flour mixture and cream again thoroughly.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken-sausage supreme
directions: Saute sausage and drain.
Saute vegetables and drain.
Cook soup according to directions.
Add 1 extra cup of water and a cup of rice.
Cook with soup until rice is tender.
Combine all ingredients.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Mix well.
Bake in deep casserole dish one hour or until brown.
Drain grease from top when done.

title: turkey in brown paper bag
directions: Mix all ingredients together and baste on turkey. Wet brown paper bag inside, then put turkey in it and cook at 350° for 30 minutes per pound.
Make sure you put a baking pan under paper bag.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: good london broil
directions: Marinate your London broil for 4 hours or longer.
Broil on 350°, or it's great on the grill!
Baste as it cooks with marinade sauce.

title: country chili
directions: Brown sausage, ground beef, onion and bell pepper; drain off excess grease.
Transfer mixture to large soup kettle.
Add chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in diced tomatoes and chili.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine butter, salt, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese. Stir well, then mix with thawed potatoes.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until bubbly and brown on top.
Can be made in advance.
Serves 6.

title: peach cobbler with praline biscuits
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil and cook 1 minute, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Pour into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and set aside.
Combine butter, brown sugar and pecans; set aside.
Combine flour and 2 teaspoons sugar; cut in shortening or butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Add buttermilk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to a 12 x 8-inch rectangle; spread with pecan mixture, leaving a 1/2-inch border.
Starting with long side, roll up jellyroll fashion.
Cut roll into 1/2-inch slices; arrange slices over peach mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: crisp sugar drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Combine egg with vinegar, lemon rind and vanilla.

title: dough for strudel
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Knead in bowl (until arm is tired)
then divide into 6 parts.
Brush with melted oleo, cover and
let rest in warm place for about 20 minutes.
Roll out
on floured cup towel and stretch where necessary.
Brush oleo
on rolled
out
dough.
Sprinkle
with
crumbs (crushed vanilla wafers
and bread crumbs or corn flakes).
Add slices apples
with skin.
Sprinkle with at least 1/2 cup of cinnamon sugar.
Add pecans and coconut in layers.
Then roll into log, pinch ends and brush with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Butter and sprinkle sugar on top.

title: jalapeno cornbread meal
directions: Brown and set aside beef and onion.
Make batter of remaining ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased baking dish.
Put beef mixture on top of batter.
Pour salsa on top of beef.
Add layer of shredded cheese.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Mix water, sugar and vinegar together.
Put ham and the mixture in crock-pot and cook on low for several hours.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo or butter in glass dish or pan.
Mix the ingredients together to make a batter (except the fruit).
Pour batter into dish with melted butter.
Put fruit on top of batter.
Batter will come to top and form a crust when baked.
Bake in 350° oven until brown on top.
Very good served warm with ice cream.

title: dijon hollandaise dip
directions: Blend in blender egg yolks, lemon juice, garlic powder and cayenne; blend for 3 seconds.
Slowly add melted butter, blending until smooth.
Chill.
Before serving, stir in sour cream and Dijon mustard.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.
Serve with assorted vegetables.

title: barb's sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add oil and egg to creamed ingredients. Add vanilla, then dry ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Dip glass in sugar and flatten balls. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chili with rice
directions: Cook and stir meat, pepper and seasoning mix in large skillet until meat is brown.
Stir in water, beans and tomato sauce. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes. Stir in corn.
Return to boil.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine
potatoes, salt and marshmallows.
Have peanuts ready on	waxed
paper or board.	Drop mixture by tablespoons onto nuts;
roll into balls.
Pan-fry in hot shortening until lightly browned.
Makes 15 to 20 small balls.

title: hot crab cocktail spread
directions: Thoroughly combine cream cheese with milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain and flake crab meat.
Add to cream cheese mixture, along with onion.
Turn into greased 8-inch pie plate or small, shallow baking dish.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until heated through.
Keep spread warm over candle or on hot tray.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate chip caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, melted margarine and 2/3 cup evaporated milk.
Batter will be thick.
Spread 1/2 of batter into pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In skillet, beat butter and garlic until sizzling.
Dip shrimp in egg and quickly drop in skillet.
Saute quickly over high heat 2 to 4 minutes.
Add white wine, salt and pepper.
Serve over a bed of rice.
Makes 5 servings.

title: pink cloud
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Cut into squares for serving when frozen.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine butter, sugar and water in small saucepan and bring just to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips plus extract; stir constantly until chocolate melts.
Place chocolate mixture in large bowl.
Beat in eggs by adding one at a time.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda in a small bowl.
Gradually add dry ingredient mixture to the chocolate batter.
Add nuts.
Spread batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 50 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 4 dozen 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: tuna and rice casserole
directions: Mix well all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes (depends on oven) at 350°.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Brown venison and drain. Cook egg noodles according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onions and peppers in skillet.
Add browned venison, soup, milk and mushrooms and mix well.
Heat through.
Remove from heat.
Season to taste and stir in sour cream.
Mix well. Serve over noodles.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, celery and bell pepper.
Drain and add soy sauce.
Add cooked rice; mix well.
Turn heat to low. Place lid on skillet and steam for 10 minutes.
Add more soy sauce when served, if needed.

title: breakfast strata
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease off.
Line a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish with the sausage.
Break bread into bite size pieces and spread over top of sausage.
Sprinkle grated cheese over sausage layer.
Beat eggs, salt, mustard and milk; pour this mixture over the cheese layer.
Pour melted butter over top.
Put in refrigerator and leave overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese; beat hard.
Drop dough by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick mexican corn bread
directions: Make corn bread batter as directed on package.
Stir in corn. Brown meat in skillet.
Remove meat from skillet, draining meat well.
Pour half of batter into skillet on top of meat drippings. Add meat, cheese, onion and peppers.
Top with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: northern bean soup
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight in cold water.
Next day, drain and cook in 1 1/2 quarts water until tender.
Drain again.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
May need to add more mayonnaise if too dry.

title: rolls
directions: In a large bowl, which is capable of being covered tightly, beat egg; add salt, cooking oil and sugar.
Blend well.
Add 1 cup hot water.
Blend well.
Add 2 cups flour.
Blend well . Add yeast and blend well.
Add 2 more cups flour and blend.
Cover and refrigerate.
When doubled in size, punch down dough.
Form rolls by hand or roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip half of roll in butter and fold over.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Allow to rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Bake until golden brown in a 425° oven.

title: banana split pie
directions: Slice banana on crust.
Put pineapple on top of banana.
Mix milk with Jell-O pudding.
Pour Cool Whip on top of pudding mix. Put in freezer for 1 hour.

title: wyatt's pecan delight pie
directions: Beat first three ingredients until stiff; fold in cracker crumbs and pecans.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan with butter and pour in mixture.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
When cool, top with sweetened whipped cream.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and chili powder together, then drain and add the next 6 ingredients.
Heat thoroughly and pour over the Doritos chips.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips and bark in double boiler.
Add peanuts and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set until cool and firm.

title: cream cheese and pecan pound cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Cream butter and cream cheese in mixer bowl until light. Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in vanilla and remaining 1 cup pecans.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 60 minutes.

title: russian borschte
directions: Fill 6-quart pot with 5 quarts of water.
Add diced vegetables.
Boil until vegetables are tender (1 1/2 hours).
If you use canned beets, do not add them until last 5 minutes.
When adding beets, heat just to boiling, otherwise soup will lose its bright red color.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; beat just until blended. Combine flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture and beat at low speed.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing to kitchen countertop.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook egg whites, sugar, flour, cocoa, milk and butter until thick; stir until real thick.
Pour into baked pie shell; cool. Put Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle mini chocolate chips on top.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over medium heat until thick. Add 1 tablespoon butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into a cool, baked pie crust.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Put chicken on top.
Mix soup, cheese, mayo and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and salsa soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine water, chicken broth, chicken and chili powder.
Bring to a boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 8 minutes.
Add corn and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.
Stir in salsa and heat through.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with chips.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chili taco salad
directions: Brown beef, chicken or turkey; add beans and seasoning mix. Simmer 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Prepare salad by layering shredded lettuce, chili mixture, chopped tomatoes, shredded Cheddar cheese and sliced red onion.
Ring with tortilla chips.

title: slush(alcohol)
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Add frozen concentrate; stir until dissolved.
Add alcohol.
Freeze, stirring often.

title: quick cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage in slices and boil in salted water for 10 minutes. Mix soup with milk, add to cabbage.
Spread American cheese over top.
Cover cheese with bread crumbs and melted butter mixed together.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: calipso pie
directions: Soften ice cream and pack into pie shell. Smooth out top. Place in freezer. Place remaining ingredients in pan (except for vanilla and nuts). Cook until soft ball forms in cup. Stir often. When thick, place pan in cold water and stir until cold. Add vanilla and nuts. Pour over ice cream and return to freezer. Enjoy!

title: veal or chicken marsala
directions: Pound veal (or chicken) until thin. Dredge lightly on both sides with flour. In large skillet, melt butter and saute mushrooms over medium heat until browned. Remove and set aside. Add veal to skillet and cook through, 4 minutes on each side. Remove to serving platter. Return mushrooms to pan. Stir in cooking wine, water, parsley and rosemary. Heat and pour over veal.

title: chocolate camelia leaf
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a bowl over hot water (not boiling water).
Choose camelia leaf.
Use a small brush to brush the leaves with melted chocolate.
Before the chocolate is set, sprinkle multi-colored sprinkles.
When chocolate is hardened, peel the chocolate from the leaves.
Leaves may be re-used.

title: granny evelyn's cheese straws
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl to make a stiff dough.
You may need to add a little more ice water to make dough workable, but don't add enough to make it sticky.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, oil, vanilla, salt, cinnamon, soda, baking
powder and flour.
Mix well and add zucchini and nuts. Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes. Fill loaf pans half full.

title: cherry nut miniatures
directions: Cream softened cheese, margarine and 1/3 of sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
