Add dry ingredients, rest of sugar, nuts and cherries.
Mix well.
Bake in miniature muffin pan at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until light brown.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat beans in juice.
Heat soup and chopped cheese in pan; drain beans.
Add to mixture.
In another pan, saute onion and add to mixture, leaving oleo in pan.
Crumble crackers and mix with oleo; pour over top of mixture.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: cold pizza
directions: Spread cream cheese on large plate.
Cover with salsa.
Top with mushrooms, then olives, then cheese.
Serve with Fritos.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Grind cucumbers, carrots and onion.
Press vegetable mixture well to remove juice.
Mix well cream cheese, mayonnaise, dash of pepper and salt to taste.
Add vegetables to cream cheese mixture and mix well.
Keeps weeks in refrigerator.

title: congealed coca-cola cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve orange gelatin in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and blend well.
Add plain gelatin.
Add remaining ingredients and stir just to blend.
Spray an 8 cup mold with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour mixture into mold.
Chill.
When mixture begins to gel, stir to distribute nuts evenly.
Continue to chill until firm.
Garnish with dollop of sour cream.

title: rhubarb triumph pie
directions: Combine strawberries, pineapple and rhubarb.
Sprinkle with tapioca and sugar mixture.
Put in pie crust; dot with 3 tablespoons butter.
Brush top crust with milk.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: In medium bowl, stir together flour and salt.
With pastry blender, cut in shortening to size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water over some of the flour-fat mixture.
Toss this portion lightly with a fork until moistened; push to side of bowl. Repeat until all of the dry mixture is moistened and clings together when pinched with fingers.
Form in ball.
Place on lightly floured surface; flatten.
Roll from center until 1/8-inch thick.
Fit loosely into pie plate.
Trim 1/2 inch beyond edge; fold under and flute.
Makes single 8 or 9-inch crust.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add carrots, raisins, pecans, coconut and apples.
Spoon into paper lined muffin pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes more than 2 dozen. May be frozen.

title: cucumber potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in
salted water in a very large saucepan until very soft.	Place
sieve
over a large bowl.
Pour potatoes and liquid into sieve and force potatoes through.
Return to saucepan. Stir in cucumber, pepper, cream, milk and onion. Simmer gently for about 5 minutes or until cucumber is tender. Add dill, salt and
pepper.
Serve
hot
or
cold.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: angel lemon pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy; add cream of tartar.
Beat until peaks, then gradually add 1 cup sugar while beating.
Beat until stiff and glossy.
Fill in well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Put in cool oven.
Bake at 250° or 275° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Add soda to buttermilk and add to cream mixture alternately with mixture of sifted dry ingredients.
Add jam, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Pour into two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground meat. Add taco seasoning and stir.
Add peppers, beans, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until creamy. Add egg and then rest of the ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet, spreading the dough slightly.
Bake at 375° from 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: chinese hot and sour soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the chicken broth, straw mushrooms, bamboo shoots, small sliced onion, vinegar, soy sauce, red pepper and whole peppers.
Bring to boiling, then reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine and 3/4 cup milk until blended, then add eggs, remainder of milk and vanilla. Beat well. Bake in 2 layer pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix cake mix, eggs, water, pudding mix, orange juice and oil.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Place 2/3 of batter in pan.
With remaining batter, mix the chocolate syrup and pour on top.
Do not stir.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: low-fat apple pie
directions: Mix with fork; roll out on floured waxed paper.
Slide dough into pie pan.
Important:
You can roll this dough out only one time.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: On top of stove brown chicken; add pinch of pepper.
Add soup and water.
Cover and let simmer 1 hour.
Cook egg noodles.
Serve egg noodles covered with chicken and gravy sauce.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and oleo in pan over low heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator to cool dough.
It will roll better.
Shape into balls.
Melt chocolate and wax in top of double boiler.
Place balls in freezer to harden.
Dip each ball in chocolate.
Place in refrigerator until chocolate hardens.

title: arroz con leche paraguaya(rice pudding)
directions: Wash rice. Put it in milk in pan and bring to a slow boil, stirring constantly. Add sugar and vanilla.
Continue cooking on a low flame until rice is soft.

title: finnish pulla bread
directions: Scald milk, then cool until warm.
Dissolve in yeast.
Add beaten eggs.
Add salt and 1 cup gluten flour.
Beat well.
Add melted butter and then add rest of gluten flour.
Beat well.
Add sugar, cardamon and raisins; knead 2 cups of white flour into dough.
Add more if necessary.
Should be soft.
Knead 20 minutes. Divide and make 2 braids.
Let rise on floured cookie sheets 1 1/2 hours until doubled in size.
Glaze with beaten eggs and raw sugar. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix all according to cake mix box. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or longer in greased and floured bundt pan.

title: waffles or pancakes
directions: Heat waffle iron while mixing.
Combine in order given, except 1 tablespoon milk.
Add it after mixing.

title: pickled cabbage
directions: Grate head of cabbage in food processor.
Dice celery and pepper.
Add celery seed.
Dissolve the sugar and salt thoroughly in the vinegar and water.
This stores in the refrigerator very well.
Just use enough to liberally coat the grated cabbage. Refrigerate several hours.
Stir once or twice to season well. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate layer bars
directions: Combine chocolate bits, cream cheese and evaporated milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bits are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in walnuts and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Blend well.
Set aside. Combine other ingredients in large bowl.
Blend with mixer until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press half of mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs over filling.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, peas, celery and onions.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, soy sauce, curry powder and garlic salt.
Chill.
Add noodles to tuna mixture.
Add mayonnaise mixture and toss. Sprinkle almonds on top.
If desired, add sliced water chestnuts.

title: texican taters
directions: Saute turkey and onion 5 to 8 minutes.

Stir in 1 teaspoon salt, chili powder and salsa. Cook 5 minutes. Cut tops off potatoes. Remove pulp, reserving shells. Add milk, sour cream, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper to potatoes. Whip until smooth. Fold in turkey mixture and half of cheese. Spoon into potato shells. Top with remaining cheese. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Clean and wash fully ripe fruit.
Mix Sure-Jell with fruit in 6 or 8-quart saucepan.
Place over high heat and stir until mixture comes to a hard boil.
At once add sugar.
Bring to a full, rolling boil that cannot be stirred down.
Boil hard one minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and skim off foam. Stir and skim five minutes to cool slightly and prevent floating fruit.
Ladle into glasses, leaving 1/2-inch space at top.
Cover jam immediately with 1/8-inch hot paraffin.

title: shrimp paste
directions: Combine all ingredients about 10 hours before serving.

title: cheesecake (2)
directions: Combine all but 1 c. of cake mix with oil and 1 egg. Mix until it crumbles. Press in bottom and halfway up sides of cake pan.

Blend softened cream cheese and sugar. Add remaining 3 eggs and the remaining cake mix. Beat 1 minute at medium speed. On low speed add milk, lemon juice, and vanilla. Mix until smooth. Pour into crust and bake at 300° for 45-50 minutes or until done. Let cool and top with pie filling. Keep refrigerated.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and salt together.
Dip chicken into butter and then roll in breadcrumb mixture.
After putting chicken in baking dish, put 1 teaspoon of butter on top of each piece.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
(Be sure to preheat oven.)

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, bananas, sour cream and lemon juice.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture just until flour mixture is moistened.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.

title: honeyed nuts
directions: Boil sugar, honey and water until syrup forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Stir in walnuts until syrup becomes thick and creamy.

title: boiled lobster
directions: Bring water to boil.
When water is boiling, rapidly plunge lobsters in, head first, one at a time.
Return to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 8 minutes for smaller lobster (1 to 1 1/4 pounds) and 10 minutes for larger lobsters (1 1/2 to 2 pounds).

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Brown hamburger
and
chopped onion.
In a baking dish, layer chilies,
meat
and
cheese;
repeat.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk, flour and seasonings until creamy.
Pour over meat. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.	Has the consistency of a souffle.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Soak potatoes several hours in a bowl of water.
Grate the potatoes and mix with the remaining ingredients.
Pour a little oil in a frying pan; drop potato batter by spoonfuls into hot oil and brown on both sides.
Keep warm while all are being prepared.
Good with sauerbraten, pot roast, etc.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hand lotion
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour up in containers.

title: french peas
directions: Cover the bottom and sides of a 10-inch skillet with some of the moist lettuce leaves.
Top with peas, green onions, sugar, salt and pepper and dot with butter.
Cover skillet and cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove lettuce leaves.
Toss peas well before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook up all carrots until barely done and drain.
Then chop up onion and bell pepper and add to carrots.
Mix rest of the ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Let cool, then pour the mixture over the carrots, onion and pepper.
Place in refrigerator and marinate for 12 hours or longer.
It will keep for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend well.
Mix with grated cabbage.
May also add grated carrot and minced celery.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Beat the eggs gently with sugar.
Add oil, 1/4 cup water and pumpkin.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° for an hour in 3 loaf pans or 3 to 4 muffin pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook onions, celery and peppers in greasy broth or oleo.
Cook chicken and debone.
Cook noodles until partly done in broth.
Mix all, but chicken.

title: roughy almondine
directions: Poach filets 4 minutes in simmering water.
Drain and dry thoroughly on paper towels.
Whip egg white until stiff.
Fold in yogurt, almonds and orange rind.
Coat drained filets with egg white mixture.
Broil until brown and puffy (about 2 to 3 minutes).

title: baked beans and beef
directions: Brown beef in pan.
Pour off fat.
Add all other ingredients. Let marinate overnight if possible.
Place in covered casserole. Add strips of bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring bouillon to a boil; stir in cornstarch mixture.
Remove from heat.
With chopstick in one hand, stir the soup.
With the other hand, slowly pour the beaten egg into soup, stirring to create egg shreds.
Remove from heat.
Put ginger in soup bowl and add soup.
Top with scallion.
Serve at once.
Yield:
1 serving.

title: coconut pie (2)
directions: Mix well.
Put in double boiler.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cook for approximately 45 minutes or until it begins to thicken.
Stir in coconut to taste.
(This may be too much for some.)
Add margarine.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Beat egg whites for topping.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 1 hour.
Cool about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the sugar and peaches.
Store at room temperature, covering loosely with cheesecloth or a clean towel.
(Do not store airtight or in the refrigerator or freezer.) Stir every day for a total of 10 days.

title: old time coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, stir mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, celery salt, salt and pepper until well combined.
Add cabbage, carrots and onion.
Toss gently to coat well.
Chill covered at least 1 hour. Toss gently before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Combine reserved pineapple juice with jello in saucepan and stir in water.
Heat to boiling, stirring to dissolve jello.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Add lemon juice and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture partially thickens.
Blend in sour cream.
Fold in pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart gelatin mold.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli cheese cornbread
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Pour over melted margarine and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot filling
directions: Mix well.
If too dry, add a little water.
Spray crock-pot with Pam.
Place filling in pot and cook on high until pot feels very warm to touch.
Turn on low for remainder of cooking time (approximately 3 hours total cooking time).
Stir once during cooking.

title: clay dough
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Slowly add water and oil.
Knead the dough well.
Roll out the dough and cut with cookie cutters. Be sure to put small hole in top for string for hanging.
Leave the cut-outs out to air dry.
When thoroughly dry and hard you can paint to decorate.
Spray with a polyurethane coating.

title: ruby red cranberry vinegar
directions: Rinse cranberries and place in a large glass jar.
Combine vinegar, honey and cinnamon sticks in a medium saucepan; simmer for 5 minutes.
Let cool until mixture is warm to the touch, not hot.
Pour over berries.
Be sure to include cinnamon sticks. Cover jar; let mixture sit for 1 to 2 weeks.
Strain vinegar and pour into a clean decorative bottle.

title: prosciutto ham with jumbo prawns
directions: Wrap 1 piece large Prosciutto around 1 large boiled, peeled prawn.
Skewer each prawn.
Briefly grill over an outdoor grill or under the broiler until Prosciutto gets a bit crispy.
Serve either on or off skewers.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Turn out on cookie sheet.
(Cool in pan about 10 minutes before turning out.)
When cool, split in half.
(Use a piece of thread or dental floss.)

title: savory potato bake
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and mustard.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 1 cup cheese; stir until melted.
Stir in potatoes, meat and onions; spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese; continue baking until cheese melts.

title: cherry pineapple dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan; pour in 1 can cherry pie filling.
Add crushed pineapple and juice.
Sprinkle on top 1 box cake mix.
Top with layer of chopped nuts and layer of coconut flakes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bean salad
directions: Bring to a boil vinegar, salad oil and sugar and pour over green beans, yellow beans, red kidney beans and lima beans or French onion rings.
Put in a covered container and mix.
Let stand or turn at least overnight.

title: blue cheese meatballs
directions: Combine meat with cheese, green onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
Cook in butter until cooked through.
When cooked, remove with slotted spoon and put in serving dish.
Add whipping cream to pan drippings.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, about 5 minutes.
Spoon glaze over meatballs.

title: brett's barbecued tuna steaks
directions: Lightly coat tuna steaks with butter.
Add chopped, raw onions, pepper to taste, dash of fresh garlic and cover with lemon juice.
Wrap tuna in foil, shiny side in.
Place on barbecue grill for 7 or 8 minutes each side.

title: june punch
directions: Make syrup by boiling sugar and 4 cups water for 10 minutes. Add tea and fruit juice concentrates.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: easy party cheese balls
directions: Mix cream cheese with dressing.
Form into balls (1 or 2). Roll in bacon bits to cover balls; chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: monroe munchies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture.
Blend in coconut, oats and flakes.
Drop from teaspoon 3-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potluck vegetable casserole
directions: You can prepare this casserole ahead and chill.
Then just add 15 minutes to baking time.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put in large bowl in layers in order given.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss when ready to serve. Serves 12 to 15.

title: whiskey sour
directions: Blend and put in freezer in covered plastic bowl.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 1/2 minute. Add blueberries. Put in greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: shoofly pie
directions: Mix into crumbs the flour, brown sugar and shortening.
Keep out 1/2 cup crumbs to sprinkle on top of pie.
Combine remaining crumbs with the egg, table syrup, hot water and baking soda.
Pour this into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: amish tapioca pudding
directions: Drain fruit and set aside.
Add water to fruit syrup to make 6 cups.
Bring to a boil and add tapioca.
Let stand 15 minutes. Add gelatin, sugar and salt.
When mixture is cool, stir in pineapple, oranges and Cool Whip.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown
ground
beef
and
onion in salad oil (drain off fat). Add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 1/2 hours.

title: grandma's taters
directions: Peel potatoes. Wash. Cut each one into cubes. Put into large boiler. Cover with water and boil until nearly tender. When potatoes are nearly tender, put oleo, salt and pepper. Put corn meal into 8 ounce cup. Put enough sweet milk into cup with meal to make a thin paste. Mix together real good. Pour all of this slowly into potatoes. Finish cooking on low heat, stirring often. May need to add more water, if too thick.

title: harper's chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Stir often to break up hamburger.
Dump everything except spices in 2 1/2 gallon kettle. Mix all spices together.
When hamburger is brown or done, drain off grease and add to kettle.
Heat to boiling and then add 2/3 of the spices and simmer 1 hour.
Taste and add more spices if needed.
Simmer 1 to 2 more hours.

title: tomato chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low and simmer an additional 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until thickened and reduced to about 2 1/2 cups.	May keep chilled and covered 3 months.

title: fellowship potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add cream cheese and sour cream using an electric mixer.
Slowly add milk; blend well.
Put in buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Brush top with melted butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick rolls
directions: Combine water and yeast.
Mix until yeast is dissolved.
Add egg, slightly beaten, sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Add flour and blend well (dough will be thin).
Place without letting rise, in greased muffin tins, filling 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 18 to 24 rolls.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Set oven on broil.
Mix all ingredients and form into a large steak on broiler grill.
Place grill 3 to 4 inches away from broiler unit.
Broil 10 to 15 minutes on each side.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix and spread filling on ham slice; roll.
Slice roll into 1/4-inch slices.
Hold together with toothpicks.

title: stir-fry string beans
directions: In a small saucepan, boil cube until dissolved.
Combine all remaining ingredients in wok or fry pan.
Add bouillon juice.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a well-greased 8-inch pie pan.
Combine 1/4 cup of sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes.

title: swedish heirloom cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter until light and fluffy.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar and salt and cream well.
Blend in flour.
Add water and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Shape into 1-inch balls and slightly flatten.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes, until done.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: spinach
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Cover with water and let set for 30 minutes.
Drain off liquid.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix broccoli and soup in a saucepan.
Stir and simmer.
Add Cheez Whiz, onion and celery; mix well.
Add cooked rice.
Heat in a greased 2-quart covered casserole dish 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a bowl place graham cracker crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Blend well.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of mixture for garnishing.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom and sides of greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill in freezer while preparing the filling.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add water, vinegar and salt to egg.
Mix with first mixture.
Blend well.
Rolls out very nicely. Easy to work with.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onions. Mix brown sugar, catsup, vinegar, dry mustard, salt, lima beans, pork and beans and red beans. Cut up hot dogs (or summer sausage). Mix all ingredients together. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Can also use electric skillet or a slow cooker.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put the salt over the cucumbers and onions and let set for 1 hour.
Drain well and add sugar, vinegar and celery seed by pouring over the vegetables.
Do not heat.
Stir the ingredients to mix celery seed.
Place in uncovered bowl in refrigerator.

title: cheese and macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix all other ingredients together. Put in macaroni and mix well.
Put into buttered dish, topped with 3 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Mix all first 5 ingredients.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in a glass of cool water.
Remove from heat and mix in marshmallow and walnuts.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, top each breast with 2 slices ham and cheese.
Combine soup and wine (do not dilute).
Spoon over chicken.
Add melted margarine to bread crumbs; sprinkle over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: filled omelet
directions: Mix eggs slightly.
Combine with bacon, cheese, sour cream and chives and cook the same as French omelet.
Serves 2.

title: swiss-ham ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli.
In large bowl, combine margarine, parsley, onion, mustard and lemon juice.
Add cheese, broccoli and ham.
Mix lightly; set aside.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Sprinkle with paprika after placing in serving dish.

title: peachie pudding bake
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Peel peaches and slice into large bowl. Sprinkle evenly with sugar and let stand 10 minutes. Stir in Bisquick and nutmeg.
Turn mixture into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Cut and mix lettuce, tomatoes, onion and avocados.
Put in a salad bowl.
Drain water off beans.
Add beans, ground beef and cheese to salad mixture. Top with salad dressing.

title: sweet hot pickles
directions: Pour off juice and slice pickles into a large jar, alternating with sugar, minced garlic and Tabasco sauce.
After 10 days, shaking jars everyday, then put them in jars or just leave in jug.

title: brandy walnut cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add 6 egg yolks (lightly beaten).
Mix together milk, brandy and vanilla.
Add alternately with flour and salt to mixture.
Add 2 cups of nuts.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Add egg and remaining ingredients.
Stir and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: "light" chocolate-grand marnier cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan and put aside.
Using a food processor, mix the cream cheese and next 6 ingredients together until smooth.
Add egg and process until blended.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Slowly pour mixture over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake is set.
Let cool in pan on wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Remove sides of pan and onto a serving platter.

title: no peek stew
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place meat on bottom of pan, then add your vegetables.
Mix together tapioca, sugar, salt and garlic salt; sprinkle mixture on top of vegetables.
Pour V-8 juice over. Cover with foil and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
"Don't peek."

title: brenda's lasagna
directions: Boil noodles.
Place noodles, meat and cheese in layers until the top of the pan.
Add spices.
Pour Ragu sauce on top.
Bake pan in oven until cheese melts.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring water, pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Add jello; let set until mixture congeals.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Add the cream cheese mixture to the jello mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour into a mold.
Refrigerate until firm in mold.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, bell pepper, cream cheese and 1/2 c. salsa in saucepan on low heat until cream cheese is melted. Spoon 1/3 c. chicken mixture down center of each tortilla and roll up. Place seam side down, in lightly greased 12X8 inch baking dish. Stir velveeta and milk in saucepan on low heat until smooth. Pour sauce over tortillas. Cover with foil. Bake at 350 degree for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Pour remaining salsa over tortillas serve hot.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Saute onions in 4 tsp. oil until clear.
Mix all ingredients and place in 11 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: finest barbecue sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together the packed brown sugar, cornstarch and chili powder. Stir the tomato sauce, vinegar, catsup and dark corn syrup into the brown sugar mixture in the saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup water.

Bring the mixture to boiling. Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir the orange juice into the tomato sauce mixture. Return the mixture to boiling. Reduce the heat. Simmer the sauce, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.
Baste the barbecue sauce over your favorite meat or poultry about the last quarter of the grilling or broiling time.
Heat through any additional sauce and pass it to spoon over each serving.
Store any remaining sauce, covered, in the refrigerator.
Makes 3 servings.
Serving size:
1 cup. Preparation time:
45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir flour, salt, sugar and butter into corn.
Beat eggs.
Add well beaten eggs to milk.
Stir into corn mixture.
Pour into a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Stir twice while baking.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
If it still appears to be runny in center, bake an additional 5 minutes or until set.

title: ham and cheese dip
directions: Have cheese spread at room temperature.
Place all ingredients in small mixer bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Put into serving dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill.

title: aunt lila's creamed potato soup
directions: Put potatoes and onion in large pot.
Add just enough water to cover potatoes and cook until soft.
Drain liquid from potatoes, leaving about 1/2 cup of liquid in the pot.
Add margarine and whip with mixer until creamy.
Add milk.
Add salt as desired. (You may use more or less of onion and margarine according to taste.)
After adding milk you will have to reheat before eating.

title: texas fudge cake
directions: Melt oleo with water and cocoa.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt and soda.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add chopped onions and green pepper.
Simmer.
Add tomatoes, soup, chili powder and paprika. Simmer until well blended.
Add kidney beans and reheat.
Freezes well.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruits and place in an oblong dish with pears turned up; place cherry in each half.

title: zucchini crab cakes
directions: Grate zucchini and squeeze out liquid with hand.
Combine zucchini and onions with salt, pepper and eggs.
Shape into patties, cover with Progresso bread crumbs.
Fry patties in a skillet with butter.

title: ten-layer cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour, shortening, milk and vanilla in large mixer bowl; beat well.
Pour 3 tablespoons batter into each of 10 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 400° for 4 to 5 minutes or until light brown.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Spread frosting between layers and over top of cake. Yield:
12 servings.

title: party chili
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and beef in a little hot oil.
Add beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, bay leaf, paprika and cayenne.
Cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add extra bean liquid or water, if needed.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and place into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool cake completely.

title: stuffed tofu with pork
directions: Chop bamboo shoots, chung choi, water chestnuts and onion finely.
Add shrimp, pork and salt and mix well.
Cut tofu into 3 slices, then into 4 equal squares.
Slit 1 corner of each piece and stuff with mixture.
Arrange in pan, add seasoning and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: individual quiches
directions: On floured surface, roll half of pastry into 12-inch circle. Cut six 4-inch circles.
Repeat with remaining pastry.
Fit into twelve (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups.
Fill each with some shrimp, onion and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients; pour over cheese.

title: tomatoes for cooking
directions: You will need canning jars, lids and rings.

title: blueberry delights
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Add eggs, vanilla and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Put cupcake papers in muffin tin.
Place one vanilla wafer in bottom.
Spoon mixture in cupcake paper about 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes.
Top with blueberry pie filling.

title: nut and honey cake
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and ground cloves in a bowl.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter and set aside.
Add broccoli and Cheez Whiz.
Combine rice, soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Combine all. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet sauerbraten
directions: Using rolling pin, finely crush cookies in a plastic bag. Add beef strips to bag.
Shake to evenly coat.
In a large skillet, in hot oil, cook beef until lightly browned.
Add soup, water and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Add any remaining crumbs from bag.
Stir to blend.
Simmer 1 minute. Serve with mashed potatoes or noodles.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed camel
directions: Be sure to use a fresh camel, the frozen variety has a gamey taste.
Most experts say the one-hump camel is far tastier than the two-humper.
Skin and clean the camel and lamb; pluck the chickens.
Boil up the rice.
Shell the nuts and seeds; fry them brown and mix them with the rice.
Hard-boil your eggs, peel 'em, chop 'em and throw 'em in.
Next, stuff the chickens with this mixture, then stuff the lamb with the chickens.
(If company's coming, you might want to add a half-dozen or so more chickens.) Stuff the camel with the lamb that's been stuffed with the stuffed chickens.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° until brown.
(Oven too small, try the clothes dryer!)
When it's done, spread the remaining rice mixture on a rather large platter and place the camel in the middle.
Decorate with a sprig of fresh parsley and serve.
I must admit I haven't tried it yet, as our neighborhood market is fresh out of camels.
So I'll file the recipe and wait until Uncle Arthur opens a Dromy-Dairy.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion and hamburger; add soups, sauce and milk.
Stir. Spoon small amount in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then add layer of tortillas.
Repeat, ending with hamburger mixture.
Sprinkle cheese and olives on top; cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Take off foil; bake another 10 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Cook the oleo, sugar and dates until mixture thickens, stirring, about 5 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and pecans.
Let cool and roll into tiny balls.
Roll in sugar when slightly dry.

title: wassail
directions: Cook on high for 2 hours in crock-pot.
Remove spices and leave drink in crock-pot.
Serve hot.
Can be refrigerated and reheated.

title: jello pie
directions: Place Jell-O in large bowl.
Put sugar in.
Pour in 1/2 the amount of boiling water the Jell-O calls for.
Mix well so it's dissolved.
Place in refrigerator until it starts to jell.
Don't let it harden too much.
In the meantime, put can of cream in freezer until it starts to slightly freeze.
Pour cream into Jell-O and whip until blended.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: raisin cake
directions: In a saucepan, boil raisins, water, sugar, butter, salt, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool. Stir in baking soda, baking powder, flour and lemon flavoring. Mix well.
Place mixture in a greased Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour at 325° or 2 large loaf pans for 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
This is a great cake.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix all cereals, nuts and pretzels together in extra large pan and set aside.
In saucepan, mix all seasoning ingredients together, stirring with wooden spoon until it reaches a boil. Pour immediately over Texas Trash, mixing well.
Bake 4 hours at 200°, stirring every 20 minutes with
wooden spoon.
Store in airtight container.
Yields approximately 4 pounds.

title: barbecued round steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in skillet.
Brown steak; simmer for 3 minutes.
Pour over before covering.
Bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.
Yields 4 servings.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar, and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each. Gradually stir in flour, cocoa, and baking powder.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for 10 minutes.
Lightly grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix cake according to package directions; pour 1/2 the batter in pan and bake 15 minutes. Meanwhile, melt caramels and margarine over low heat.
When cake is done, pour caramel mixture over warm cake.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate morsels.
Pour remaining batter over top; bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Chop all of the vegetables very fine.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill well before serving.
Keeps 1 week.

title: ham and cheese baked frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Heat Crisco oil in 10-12 inch skillet on medium heat.
Add potatoes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 tsp. salt and pepper.
Cook 8 minutes or until almost brown.
Add ham. Cook 2-3 minutes more.
Turn occasionally with spatula.
Blend eggs with milk, Italian seasoning and remaining 1 tsp. salt while potatoes are cooking.
Place the potatoes into a 9 x 13 inch casserole dish sprayed with non-stick cooking spray and stir the eggs into the potatoes.
Bake covered at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven.
Bake 15 minutes more or until cheese is melted and eggs are set.
Turn oven to broil and continue to cook about 2 minutes, or until top is nicely browned.
Allow to cool 10 minutes before cutting into 8 squares.
Serve topped with heated salsa.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly and blend into liquids.
Mix in large bowl and refrigerate.
Use amount as needed to bake. (Biscuits do not have to rise.)
Can be made ahead and stored in refrigerator.

title: toffee square cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Pat in a rectangle on an 11 x 17-inch greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Take out and immediately spread the Hershey bars (which you previously have broken into pieces) onto the cookie crust.
Let soften.
You may need to put cookie sheet back in the oven for a minute.
Spread chocolate over entire cookie crust.
Top with chopped nuts.
Cut into squares when completely cooled.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook molasses, sugar, water and salt without stirring until soft crack stage (270°).
Remove from heat.
Add butter and pour over corn.
Mix quickly and form into balls.

title: glazed donuts
directions: Heat the milk.
Pour milk into large bowl and add salt, margarine and sugar.
Mix and cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour and mix thoroughly.
Add egg and the yeast that has been dissolved in 1/2 cup water.
Mix well.
Add enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead lightly.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and lay out.
Cut with doughnut cutter and let rise 1/2 hour.
Fry in hot oil or fat.

title: easy cheese lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan on bottom only. Combine in large bowl first 3 ingredients until well mixed.
Press into prepared pan.
Blend in large bowl frosting mix and cream cheese.
Reserve 1/2 cup for frosting bars.
Add 2 eggs to remaining frosting mixture.
Beat 3 to 5 minutes.
Spread over base.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: In a fairly large bowl, mix all the spices with the oil. Add oyster crackers and stir well. Spread out in jelly roll or other large pan with sides. Bake at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring a couple of times. Cool and eat.

title: olga's meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly combine and shape into loaf, 8 x 4 x 1 1/2-inches, in shallow pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: popeye's passion
directions: Cook, drain and squeeze excess water from spinach.
Boil potatoes; slice thin and line casserole dish.
Cut remainder into small cubes.
Cut tofu into small cubes.
Mix spinach, potato soup (no milk added), curry powder, cubed potatoes and cubed tofu. Spread over thinly sliced potatoes in casserole dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: prune harvest bread
directions: Stir warm water, dry yeast, milk, honey, salt, vegetable oil and eggs together thoroughly.
Use 1/4 cup of flour to dredge prunes.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to liquid.
Add prunes and nuts.
Knead for several minutes.
Place in a greased loaf pans.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Let rise again about 1/2 hour.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.
A great holiday breakfast.

title: cherry fudge cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Butter and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine lemon juice and milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine butter, oil and sugar in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Add milk mixture, eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients; add to egg mixture, mixing well.
Stir in zucchini.
Spoon batter into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow 9 x 13 dish.
Top each breast with slice of swiss cheese.
Stir together soup and wine or water. Spoon evenly over chicken.
Coarsely crush stuffing mix and sprinkle over chicken.
Drizzle evenly with melted butter.
Bake uncovered 350 for 50 - 55 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serves 6.

title: honey bee cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, brown sugar, honey and egg in bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop the dough by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown around edges, 7 to 9 minutes.

title: auntie's caramels
directions: Melt sugar, syrup and margarine.
Add Milnot.
Cook, stirring continuously, to 250° on candy thermometer
(form hard ball in cold water).
Add nuts.
Pour into well buttered pan and cool. Cut into squares and wrap each piece in waxed paper.

title: ranch noodles with turkey
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Melt butter in skillet with Ranch dressing mix.
Add peas and carrots.
Warm through and toss with pasta and add turkey.
Serves 4.

title: crab hors d'ouevres
directions: Blend all together.
Broil 5 minutes on English muffin.
Cut into pieces to serve.
Enjoy.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° about 1 hour ahead of time.
Grease and flour 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan and bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease and flour pizza pan.
Spread sugar cookie roll over pan.
Bake at 350°.
Cool.
Mix topping, cream cheese and sugar with blender or electric beater.
Spread over cooled cookie dough. Garnish with fresh fruit:
kiwi, Mandarin oranges, strawberries, pineapple or any kind.
Put bananas on just before serving.
Top with maraschino cherries.

title: country soup supper
directions: Place meat, water, salt and pepper in a large kettle.
Slowly bring to a boil.
Skim top.
Add garlic and bay leaf.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender. Remove bay leaf.
Add all fresh vegetables, barley and tomato sauce.
Simmer, covered, about 30 minutes.
Add beans and continue simmering, covered, for another 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: onion rings
directions: Separate onions into rings; set aside.
Combine all other ingredients.
Beat just until moistened.
Using a fork, dip onion rings into batter; drain off excess.
Add to deep hot fat (375°) or saucepan.
Fry onions in single layer, stirring once with a fork to separate rings in single layer.
When onions are golden brown, 2 to 4 minutes, remove and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: quick chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together in saucepan white sugar, milk and margarine. Boil for two minutes.
Add peanut butter, cocoa and vanilla; remove from heat and mix well, then stir in oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper to harden or pour in a slightly greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: delightful greens
directions: Pick and wash greens until clean. Boil hamhocks in 4 quarts of water. Cook about 30 minutes on low heat. Add salt, dash of sugar and greens. Cook on medium heat until done.
